(4, 'Travel agency', 3, 7, 25, 'Travel agency is a job that proposes and sells package tours planned by travel agencies on behalf of customers such as individuals, companies, schools, etc. as a counter staff and sales staff.\n \nAfter firmly grasping the customer\'s purpose, request, taste, budget, etc., we will utilize a wide range of knowledge about the travel industry and propose a plan that meets the needs.\n\nIn order to sell safe and enjoyable travel, bright and sincere work is required, including store management and customer service.', 'As a window staff / sales representative, we propose and sell travel products (package tours, etc.) planned by travel agencies to customers such as individuals, companies, and schools on our behalf.\nSince there are a wide variety of products for package tours alone, we will propose a plan that meets your needs by utilizing your wide knowledge of the travel industry after understanding the purpose, needs, tastes, budget, etc. of your travel.\nWe also prepare for a safe and comfortable trip, such as booking accommodations and vehicles, and insurance procedures.\nIn order to sell safe and enjoyable travel, all personality and sincere work is required, including cleaning stores, managing pamphlets, creating decorations such as pops, and serving customers.\nA travel agency is a job that mediates and sells, unlike a travel agency that plans travel products (package tours, etc.).', 'Customer service\nForeign language conversation\nDocument editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nTravel plan creation (PC, tablet)\nOperation of reservation system (PC, tablet)\nDialogue communication\nProduct description, proposal, negotiation\nAdjustment, troubleshooting', 'Travel Business Law, Terms and Conditions\nKnowledge of tourist destinations\nKnowledge of travel and transportation', 'Travel agency', 'Counter sales\nReservation, arrangement, and sale of transportation tickets, airline tickets, boarding tickets, etc.\nAccommodation reservations, arrangements and sales\nSale and operation of package tours\nVisa and ESTA application agency\nTravel accident insurance enrollment procedure\nCollection and provision of travel information\nSale of travel tickets', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sales clerk (excluding department store clerk) (male)', '21.90', '342.00', 'Starting salary: 219,000 yen (Company size total, 20 to 24 years old)\nAverage: 285,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:53:57', NULL),
(5, 'City council member', 10, 10, 45, 'A city council member is a job that reflects the voice of citizens in the city administration.\n\nWe investigate issues in the city\'s finances, education, welfare, economy, environment, etc. on a daily basis, formulate policies, and even implement them.\n\nThere are many people who are familiar with the region and history, such as local notables and educators, and we also aim to be the first step in national affairs.\n\nIn some cases, street speeches and lectures at train stations and shopping districts appeal to citizens for ideas and bills for better city administration. To that end, we participate in festivals and civic meetings, gather the voices of citizens, and formulate bills.\n\nSince city council members are designated as public officials, there are various restrictions not only during work but also in daily life.', '≪Work in Congress≫\nParliament usually has regular meetings held four times a year in March, June, September, and December, and extraordinary sessions convened as needed.\nThe city council attends the council to deliberate and vote on the bills submitted by the mayor and other city councils, sometimes by himself, checking whether the administration is being done correctly, and questioning. If there are any points or problems, we will pursue them strictly.\nThe session (how many days the parliament will be held) will be decided on the first day of the parliament. The average number of days per year for each city council, including regular and extraordinary sessions, is approximately 87 days.\n≪Work outside the parliament≫\nOnce the council is closed, the city council will report and disseminate to the public the results of the council on what issues and how it was decided to respond through meetings, personal newspapers, blogs and Twitter.\nLet\'s get ready for Congress. We will have a deep discussion and carefully investigate the situation of the administration and the life of the citizens in order to make an appropriate decision.\nWe hold town meetings to gather the voices of citizens, listen to requests from neighborhood associations and shopping districts, and visit the city hall to receive explanations about the administration.\nGo on a tour to learn about the success stories of policies made in other cities.\nIt is also an important task to appeal to the citizens about their thoughts and policies about the city administration even in the situation of living away from the parliament.\nSince city council members are stipulated as public officials by the Public Offices Election Law, there are various restrictions on daily life, such as prohibition of gifts that are considered as donations, as well as during work.', 'Document editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nWriting\nPresentation\nDissemination of information via SNS and BLOG\nTeam management\nNetworking, network construction', 'Local politics\nPolicy\nLocal economy\nSocial issues\nLaw', 'City council\nArea', 'Information gathering\nProblem discovery\nPolicy making\nPolicy proposal\nBargaining power\nNetwork building ability', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not Applicable', '0.00', '750.00', 'Average annual income: 7.5-8 million yen', '≪ Candidate qualification≫\n 1. Being a Japanese citizen over 25 years old\n 2. Have the right to vote of the prefectural assembly members\n 3. You can submit a deposit of 600,000 yen', '19,570 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 4, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:04', NULL),
(6, 'Prefectural council members', 10, 10, 45, 'A member of the prefectural assembly is the job of making decisions on the establishment of important ordinances and budgets in each prefecture.\n\nIt is also the job of the prefectural assembly to check whether the administration is operating according to the results of the vote and to report the details of the vote to the citizens of the prefecture.\n\nWe investigate and research issues in finance, education, welfare, economy, environment, etc. every day, and formulate and implement policies.\n\nThere are many people who are familiar with the region and history, such as local notables and educators, and we also aim to be the first step in national affairs.\n\nWe sometimes appeal to the citizens for ideas and proposals for better city administration, mainly in street speeches and lectures at stations and shopping districts. Or for that purpose, participate in festivals and civic meetings, gather the voices of citizens, and make a bill.\n\nSince prefectural assembly members are designated as public officials, there are various restrictions not only during work but also in daily life.', '≪Work in Congress≫\nParliament usually has regular meetings held four times a year in February, June, September, and December, and extraordinary sessions convened as needed.\nPrefectural councils attend parliaments to deliberate and vote on bills submitted by the governor and other prefectural councils, sometimes submit their own bills, check whether the administration is working properly, and question. If there are any points or problems, we will pursue them strictly.\nThe session (how many days the parliament will be held) will be decided on the first day of the parliament. The average number of days per year for each parliament, including regular and extraordinary sessions, is approximately 85 days.\n≪Work outside the parliament≫\nWhen the council is closed, the prefectural council reports and disseminates to the prefectural citizens the results of the council on what issues and how they were to respond through meetings, personal newspapers, blogs and Twitter.\nLet\'s get ready for Congress. We will have a deep discussion and carefully investigate the situation of the government and the lives of the citizens of the prefecture in order to make an appropriate decision.\nWe hold town meetings to gather the voices of prefectural citizens, listen to requests from neighborhood associations and shopping districts, and visit prefectural offices to receive explanations about the administration.\nGo on a tour to learn about the success stories of policies made in other cities.\nIn preparation for the parliament, it is also an important task to appeal to the citizens of the prefecture about their thoughts and policies regarding the prefectural government.\nPrefectural lawmakers are stipulated as public officials by the Public Offices Election Law, so there are various restrictions on daily life, such as prohibition of gifts that are considered as donations, as well as during work.', 'Document editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nWriting\nPresentation\nDissemination of information via SNS and BLOG\nTeam management\nNetworking, network construction', 'Local politics\nPolicy\nLocal economy\nSocial issues\nLaw', 'Prefectural assembly\nArea', 'Information gathering\nProblem discovery\nPolicy making\nPolicy proposal\nBargaining power\nNetwork building ability', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not Applicable', '0.00', '780.00', 'Average annual income: 7.8-12 million yen', '≪ Candidate qualification≫\n 1. Being a Japanese citizen over 25 years old\n 2. Have the right to vote of the prefectural assembly members\n 3. You can submit a deposit of 600,000 yen', '2,687人', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 4, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:10', NULL),
(7, 'Japan Ground Self-Defense Force', 8, 2, 8, 'Land Self-Defense Force is a job to protect the people and the land in combat, information gathering, and supply on land.\n \n  Its roles are divided into three: defense activities to protect the land, emergency rescue activities to be dispatched in the event of a disaster in Japan, and international peace cooperation activities to be carried out in the event of a disaster or conflict overseas.\n \n  In addition to the above, it is also important to prepare for emergencies, to carry out regular daily life and self-management, to improve your skills, and to improve your physical strength.\n\nPublicly available and regular exercises are very popular and it is very difficult to get tickets.', 'The Self-Defense Force on land is the main task of defense activities such as combat on land, information gathering, and supply in order to directly protect the people and the land.\nDefense operations include not only units such as infantry and tank units, but also units that build roads and bridges.\nIn addition to guarding foreign state guests (important guests), there is also work such as handling unexploded ordnance.\nAs an emergency Rescue activities, he is involved in disaster dispatch such as rescue of natural disasters such as earthquakes, storms and floods, volcanic eruptions, snow damage, fires, sea accidents, aircraft accidents, rescue of victims in mountains, etc. We will cooperate with and carry out emergency Rescue activities.\nThe activities of the Ground Self-Defense Force extend not only domestically, but also overseas, such as dispatching to disasters and dispatching to UN peacekeeping operations. In conflict areas overseas, we will carry out international peace cooperation activities to maintain peace in those areas and contribute to the international community.', 'Battles in ground battles and field battles\nOperation and maintenance of vehicles and tanks\nWeapon operation and maintenance\nCollecting and transmitting information such as reconnaissance and communication\nSearch, first aid, rescue of victims and victims\nHealth management and hygiene management', '≪Ordinary course≫\nKnowledge of ground combat\n≪Armor Department≫\nKnowledge of tanks\nKnowledge of reconnaissance\n≪Special course (field) ≫\nKnowledge of field warfare\n≪Special course (high) ≫\nKnowledge of aircraft and interceptors\n≪Aviation Department≫\nKnowledge of aircraft\n≪Facilities Department≫\nKnowledge of obstacles and position building\n≪Communication Department≫\nKnowledge of communication\n≪Ordnance≫\nKnowledge of weapons\n≪Transportation Department≫\nKnowledge of vehicles and transportation\n≪Department of Chemistry≫\nKnowledge of decontamination\n≪Police Department≫\nKnowledge of order maintenance\n≪Finance Department≫\nKnowledge of accounting and accounting\n≪Information Department≫\nKnowledge of information gathering\n≪Health Section≫\nKnowledge of health and hygiene management\n≪Music Department≫\nKnowledge of music', 'Self-Defense Force\nDisaster area\nAccident site', 'Training\nstand-by\nDisaster area support\nInternational support', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Not Applicable', '0.00', '560.00', 'Average annual income transition: 5.6 million yen to 6.8 million yen', 'Entrance to the Ground Self -Defense Force Higher Technical School or older or over', '140,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 4, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:17', NULL),
(8, 'Maritime Self -Defense Force', 8, 2, 8, 'The Maritime Self-Defense Force is a task to protect Japan\'s peace and maritime traffic security in preparation for aggression from the sea.\n\nIts role is divided into three: defense activities to protect the territorial waters, emergency Rescue activities to be dispatched in the event of a disaster in Japan, and international peace cooperation activities to be carried out in the event of a disaster or conflict overseas.\n\nIn addition to the above, it is also important to prepare for emergencies, to carry out regular daily life and self-management, to improve your skills, and to improve your physical strength.\n\nThe Maritime Self-Defense Force curry, which is said to have its own secret recipe for each ship in each region, is famous, and some are sold to the general public. It is eaten every Friday, and it is said that it has its roots in eating curry every week in order to grasp the day of the week at a long-term venue that loses the sense of time.', 'We are engaged in defense activities to prevent entry into Japanese territorial waters. In cooperation with the Japan Coast Guard, we may secure the safety of maritime traffic in the surrounding sea area and secure suspicious ships.\nIn the event of a large-scale disaster such as an earthquake or typhoon, various activities such as search and rescue of victims and injured ships and aircraft, flood control, medical care, epidemic prevention (boueki), water supply, transportation of personnel and supplies, etc. We will carry out emergency rescue activities in cooperation with the police and fire department.\nThe activities of the Maritime Self-Defense Force extend not only domestically, but also overseas, such as dispatching goods, equipment and people using ships, and dispatching to the United Nations peacekeeping operations. In conflict areas overseas, we will carry out international peace cooperation activities to maintain peace in those areas and contribute to the international community.', 'Weapon operation and maintenance\nOperation and maintenance of ships, aircraft and helicopters\nMeteorological observation, ocean observation, water measurement\nAir traffic control\nSearch using sonar, radar and radio detectors\nCommunication, encryption\nDiving\nSearch, first aid, rescue of victims and victims\nHealth management and hygiene management', 'Special and high expertise is required for each of nearly 20 occupations\nKnowledge of weapons\nKnowledge of ships, aircraft and helicopters\nKnowledge of communication and cryptography\nKnowledge of sonar, radar and radio detectors\nKnowledge of air traffic control\nKnowledge of accounting and accounting\nKnowledge of meteorological observations, ocean observations, and water measurements\nKnowledge of health and hygiene\nKnowledge of first aid / rescue\nKnowledge about diving\nKnowledge of cooking\nKnowledge of music', 'Self-Defense Force\nDisaster area\nAccident site', 'Training\nStand-by\nDisaster area support\nInternational support', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Not Applicable', '0.00', '560.00', 'Average annual income transition: 5.6 million yen to 6.8 million yen', 'Entrance to the Ground Self -Defense Force Higher Technical School or older or over', '41,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 4, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:22', NULL),
(9, 'Japan Air Self-Defense Force', 8, 2, 8, 'The Air Self-Defense Force is a task to protect Japan\'s peace and air traffic security in preparation for aggression from the air.\n\nIts role is divided into three: defense activities to protect the airspace, emergency Rescue activities to be dispatched in the event of a disaster in Japan, and international peace cooperation activities to be carried out in the event of a disaster or conflict overseas.\n\nIn addition to the above, it is also important to prepare for emergencies, to carry out regular daily life and self-management, to improve your skills, and to improve your physical strength.\n\nIn recent years, the increase in scrambled launches, which is an urgent defense for fighters when there is a risk of invading the airspace, has become a problem.', 'We will guard and monitor Japanese airspace, give warnings to aircraft attempting to invade illegally, and respond promptly to move out if a foreign aircraft illegally invades Japanese airspace.\nIf a Not clear aircraft is found in the airspace, the Self-Defense Force aircraft will scramble and protect the Japanese sky.\nWe constantly monitor the airspace and monitor not only aircraft but also cruise missiles. Aircraft maintenance and air traffic control are also one of the roles of the Aviation Self-Defense Force.\nIn the event of a large-scale disaster such as an earthquake or typhoon, we will carry out emergency Rescue activities in cooperation with police and fire departments, with the task of airlifting personnel and supplies to places without airfields.\nIn the event of an aircraft accident, we will search and rescue the passengers and crew.\nThe activities of the Air Self-Defense Force extend not only domestically, but also overseas, such as dispatching goods, equipment and people using helicopters and aircraft, and dispatching to the United Nations peacekeeping operations. In conflict areas overseas, we will carry out international peace cooperation activities to maintain peace in those areas and contribute to the international community.', 'Manipulation, maintenance and loading of weapons and ammunition\nOperation and maintenance of aircraft and vehicles\nAviation weather observation and air traffic control\nConstruction and maintenance of early warning system and weather analysis forecast system\nOperation of communication electronic devices, information collection\nMaintenance and repair of runways and buildings\nSearch, rescue, and emergency for victims and victims\nHealth management and hygiene management', '≪Aviation business≫\nKnowledge of aircraft\n≪Air traffic control≫\nKnowledge of air traffic control\n≪High fire≫\nKnowledge about missiles, etc.\n≪Maintenance≫\nKnowledge of aircraft and vehicles\n≪Facilities≫\nKnowledge of runways and buildings\nKnowledge of electricity and boilers\n≪Hygiene≫\nKnowledge of health care and first aid\n≪Security≫\nKnowledge of security of facilities and members\n≪Program≫\nKnowledge of systems and programs\n≪Weather≫\nKnowledge of aeronautical meteorological observation\n≪Communication Electronics≫\nKnowledge of communication electronic equipment\n≪Armed≫\nKnowledge of weapons and ammunition\n≪Rescue≫\nKnowledge of search, rescue and emergency\n≪Music≫\nKnowledge of music', 'Self-Defense Force\nDisaster area\nAccident site', 'Training\nStand-by\nDisaster area support\nInternational support', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Not Applicable', '0.00', '560.00', 'Average annual income transition: 5.6 million yen to 6.8 million yen', 'Enroll in the Ground Self -Defense Force Higher Technical School, which is 18 years old or less or under 33 years old', '47,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 4, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:30', NULL),
(10, 'Firefighter', 8, 2, 8, 'Firefighters (firefighters) belong to the fire departments and fire departments of local governments, and are responsible for protecting the safety of people by extinguishing fires and providing emergency services.\n \nFirefighters perform Fire fighting in the event of a fire, Rescue activities in the event of an accident or disaster, First aid to transport injured or sick people, and Disaster prevention activities to prevent damage from accidents or disasters. , Five activities of Preventive activities to make sure that the structure of the building is less prone to accidents are the main missions.\n\n  In addition to the above, it is also important to prepare for emergencies, to carry out regular daily life and self-management, to improve your skills, and to improve your physical strength.\nSince 1972, the National Fire Rescue Technology Convention has been held every year in order to develop model members with that skill, and members from all over the world continue to work hard.', 'Upon receiving a fire report, we will be dispatched to the site as soon as possible to stop the fire from the fire site, and at the same time, save lives from the site and the neighborhood.\nAt the fire site, in order to minimize the spread of fire, we quickly grasp the fire situation and wind direction and take action. It also retreats nearby spectators to a safe place and removes obstacles that prevent fire extinguishing.\nRegardless of whether there is a fire or not, we are constantly training and always preparing to be dispatched so that we can rush to the fire site immediately.\nIn addition to fires, it is our duty to provide first aid to people who have been injured in general accidents (other than traffic accidents such as falls) and suddenly ill people, including traffic accidents, and transport them to medical institutions.\nIt is common for three people to ride in an ambulance, one of whom is qualified as a paramedic. First aid is provided by a paramedic.\nIn addition to fires and traffic accidents, mountain collapses and rivers are also activity sites. At the site of a mountain collapse, it is your mission to rescue those who have been buried alive by the landslide. We also perform Rescue activities even in water accidents in river areas.\nAs Disaster prevention activities, we will carry out educational activities to prevent fires. This is done to prevent disasters and prevent damage to the minimum. In case of emergency, fire extinguishers and seismic vehicles are used mainly by neighborhood associations and residents\' associations to raise awareness of disaster prevention among local residents and to let them know basic actions and evacuation routes. Then, we will provide training and guidance on initial fire extinguishing, physical protection, rescue / rescue, etc. Disaster prevention training may be held at elementary schools.\nWe assume the level of fires and earthquakes, assume damage patterns based on the topography of the region, and conduct training that suits the actual situation of each region.\nAs Preventive activities, we will rigorously examine and inspect the actual conditions of the site regarding the fire safety of the building and the installation of firefighting equipment, etc., and provide guidance based on the results.\nDuring construction or at the time of completion, we actually go to the construction site to check the construction status and strictly inspect whether the standards for fire prevention are met. We will carry out similar examinations, inspections, and guidance even when the usage is changed after completion, and strive to prevent fire and ensure safety of the building.\nThere are also staff who work in Office work, and there are many Office work jobs in the fire department that only do desk work, in addition to the members who are dispatched upon receiving a report.\nOffice work staff perform Office work tasks such as paperwork, accounting and payroll. There are many staff members at the fire department who support the staff inside the station.', 'Operation of firefighting and rescue equipment\nInvestigation and information gathering (land irrigation investigation, fire cause investigation, etc.)\nCommunication with local residents\nFirst aid\nCardiopulmonary resuscitation, AED operation\nEvacuation guidance\nOperation of communication equipment', 'Fire Service Act\nFire extinguishing knowledge\nRescue knowledge\nMedical knowledge\nPreventive knowledge\nDisaster prevention knowledge\nScientific knowledge\nCommunication knowledge', 'Fire department\nFire department', 'Fire fighting\nRescue activities\nFirst aid\nLifesaving activities\nDisaster prevention activities\nPreventive activities\nFirefighting equipment inspection\nPhysical fitness training\nTraining\nOffice work', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not Applicable', '21.20', '718.00', 'Starting salary: 212,000 yen ~ / month\nAverage annual income: 7.18 million yen', 'None', '162,124人', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 4, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:37', NULL),
(11, 'System Engineer', 1, 3, 16, 'System engineers are commonly known as SEs. It is a job to stand between the client and the development staff and manage the system development site as a conduit between them.\n\nWe have a meeting with the client to understand what kind of system we are looking for, analyze requirements and define requirements, and create proposals.\nIn addition, it designs the basic system configuration, performs detailed design for programming, and gives instructions to the programmer.\nWhen the system is completed, we will test it, and if we can confirm that there are no defects or mistakes, we will complete and deliver it.\n\nDepending on the scale of the company and the project, the project leader\'s work (budget and member management) and programming, which are higher-ranking occupations, may be done by himself, and he is an independent person who acquires communication ability in addition to a wide range of knowledge and experience. There is also.', 'Understand what kind of system the client wants and consider how to realize it.\nIn the requirement definition, we consider a system that meets the request of the requester and create a proposal or RFP (request for proposal).\nIn the basic design, the system configuration according to the requirement definition is examined and the specifications are created.\nIn the detailed design, the design is performed to program the operation according to the system configuration.\nCheck the delivery schedule to the programmer who programs the basic design and detailed design.\nWe perform unit tests for each function and integration tests to check the overall operation to see if the created program works normally, and deliver it to the client.', 'Project Management\nBusiness building literacy\nStatistical analysis\nSystem Design\nProgramming\nSystem test', 'Service planning\nSystem operation\nsystem management\nClient industry knowledge\nProgramming\nSoftware design', 'IT related companies\nSystem development company\nSoftware development company\nHome appliance maker\nGame maker\nFreelance', 'Hearing\nRequirements analysis\nRequirement definition\nbasic design\nDetailed design\nCreating programming instructions\nprogramming\nImplementation\nProgress management\nDebug, fix\ndelivery of materials\nMaintenance and operation', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'System engineer (male)', '25.40', '492.00', 'Starting salary: 254,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 410,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '922,491 IT engineers', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:43', NULL),
(12, 'Security engineer', 1, 3, 16, 'A security engineer is an information security professional who performs design, development, testing, and operation and maintenance.\n\nWe verify the safety not only in terms of safety on the system, but also in the movement and flow of people who use the system. Therefore, we will have a meeting with the client to understand what kind of system is required, analyze and define the requirements, and design the system configuration.\nProgramming is performed based on the design document, and when the system is completed, tests and countermeasures are performed to confirm that there are no defects or mistakes.\n\nWith the rapid spread and development of the Internet in recent years, the importance of information security is increasing year by year, and it is expected that the demand for security engineers will continue to increase in the future.\nSince it is an area that requires extremely advanced engineer skills and relatively new skills, the number of human resources is not large and it is a useful occupation.', 'Check the security policy, privacy policy, governance system, etc., and check how to operate system security.\nWe analyze information security risks such as information leaks caused by the characteristics and operation methods of the system, and propose countermeasures.\nBased on the suggestions, we will design a system configuration that takes security into consideration.\nBased on the design document, we will build a system, install and set security equipment and software, and build a security system.\nThe source code of the built security system is confirmed and the penetration test is performed to perform a pseudo attack to complete the system.\nAfter the system is completed, we will update security equipment and software, collect security information, and carry out regular inspections and tests so that we can always respond to new security risks.', 'Project Management\nBusiness building literacy\nHacking technology\nSystem Design\nProgramming\nSystem test', 'Information logic\nComputer engineering\nOperating system\nSecurity management\nNetwork security\nSystem security\nApplication security\nFirewall\nVirus\nSecurity protocol\nUnauthorized access method\nKnowledge of cyber attacks\nPersonal Information Protection Law\nLanguage (English)', 'IT related companies\nSystem development company\nSoftware development company\nHome appliance maker\nGame maker', 'Hearing\nRequirements analysis\nRequirement definition\nbasic design\nDetailed design\nCreating programming instructions\nprogramming\nImplementation\nProgress management\nDebug, fix\ndelivery of materials\nMaintenance and operation', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'System engineer (male)', '25.40', '492.00', 'Starting salary: 254,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 410,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '922,491 IT engineers', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:49', NULL),
(13, 'SES engineer', 1, 3, 10, 'An SES engineer is a business that belongs to the abbreviation of system engineering service engineer and is stationed in the office to perform system development work entrusted by a client under a business consignment contract to develop, operate, and maintain the system. is.\n\nBased on the contents of the outsourcing contract created at the request of the client, we will perform the work such as design, development, construction and operation necessary for the system for a certain period of time.\n\nThere is no guarantee for the deliverables, and it is a business that provides the technical capabilities and working hours required for the system held by the client.', 'The SES engineer provides the client with the technology and labor force that adapts to the contract contents based on the contents of the business consignment contract concluded with the client by the service provider called System Engineering Service.\nA system engineering service contract provides the workforce needed for the developed system, not the price for results or quality.\nSince we are hired by a business that provides SES services, we are basically not directly instructed by customers about our business, and we are required to carry out our business according to the contract details.\nThe work to be carried out is the same as the work performed by system engineers (links to system engineers), WEB programmers (links to WEB programmers), and other engineers, with the difference that results and instructions cannot be requested.', 'Statistical analysis\nSystem Design\nProgramming\nSystem Test', 'Service planning\nSystem operation\nSystem management\nClient industry knowledge\nProgramming\nSoftware design', 'IT related companies\nSystem development company\nSoftware development company\nHome appliance maker\nGame maker', 'Hearing\nRequirements analysis\nRequirement definition\nbasic design\nDetailed design\nCreating programming instructions\nprogramming\nImplementation\nProgress management\nDebug, fix\ndelivery of materials\nMaintenance and operation', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'System engineer (male)', '25.40', '492.00', 'Starting salary: 254,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 410,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '922,491 IT engineers', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 5, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:54:54', NULL),
(14, 'Network engineer', 1, 3, 15, 'A network engineer is a job that performs requirements definition, design, construction, and operation and maintenance related to networks such as the Internet and LAN.\n\nCapacity planning is performed according to the request of the requester and the requirements of the system that uses the network, and the selection of services to be used and the network configuration are determined.\nCreate a network configuration diagram, build it according to the configuration, and check the operation.\nEven in the operation phase after installation, we will perform operation and maintenance such as changing device configurations and settings, and troubleshooting. As network traffic tends to increase year by year, it is necessary to continuously improve performance and improve operational efficiency.\n\nWe are entrusted with a wide range of services, from web services connected to the Internet and LANs in offices to large-scale ones such as the Bank network and the backbone of telecommunications companies. In recent years, the number of companies that make heavy use of cloud services has expanded, the scope of business has expanded, and the number of network engineers who even develop areas has increased.', 'Network engineers are responsible for requirements definition, design, construction, and operation and maintenance of open networks such as the Internet and local area networks (LAN) such as offices and NW devices and servers connected to them.\nIn the requirement definition, the service level and the request to the network are confirmed by confirming with the requester, and the implementation method is examined.\nIn the design, we select the equipment and devices to be used, cloud services, etc., perform capacity planning according to traffic, connected devices, applications to be used, etc., and design the entire network.\nIn the construction, we prepare the devices and cloud services to be used, set the internal and external connections such as DNS and network routing, set the server to connect to, and set each other device, and perform the test.\nIn operation and maintenance, we regularly check network and server traffic, understand the characteristics of the network, and continuously consider and improve efficient operation methods that match the characteristics. It also troubleshoots such as sudden failures.', 'Building business literacy\nSystem Design\nNetwork construction\nPhysical work of network equipment\nSystem operation management\nTroubleshooting\nProject Management', 'Knowledge of networks\nKnowledge of hardware\nTelecommunications\nBasic computer design\nSecurity knowledge', 'IT related companies\nCommunication companies\nCommunication equipment company\nNetwork-related companies', 'Hearing\nsuggestion\ndesign\nconstruction\ntest\nOperational work\nMonitoring work', 1, 0, 0, 0, 'System engineer (male)', '25.40', '492.00', 'Starting salary: 254,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 410,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '922,491 IT engineers', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:01', NULL),
(15, 'Game producer', 1, 3, 17, 'A game producer is a job that oversees the planning and completion of a game.\n\nWhat kind of games are popular now and are likely to be popular in the future? We will conduct market investment and analysis, and consider and decide what kind of genre of games to sell and how to sell them.\nWe select the production staff necessary for successful game development, raise development costs, perform sales promotion production, and when ready, we are in charge of schedule management etc. and supervise the whole.\n\nIn recent years, social games using smartphones have expanded, and the demand for game producers has increased. In addition, the number of service designs that incorporate the concept of games such as gamification is increasing, and the fields of activity are expanding beyond games.', 'What kind of games are popular now and are likely to be popular in the future? We perform market investment and analysis. We focus not only on game-related information, but also on trends in the entertainment industry or society as a whole, and analyze and make predictions from a business perspective, such as the relationship between users and games in future society.\nWe will make a plan and business plan such as what kind of game will be sold to which target, at what price and price system, and by what means, and decide on the development of the title.\nSelect the production staff needed for successful game development, such as directors, scenariowriters, game programmers, and designers. Directs production and development.\nWe carry out test marketing with a test monitor to improve quality and formulate effective release promotion.\nAt the time of release, we will direct the promotion such as coverage, press release, advertisement placement etc. to the front. At the same time, we will strive to approach many users by utilizing SNS and so on.', 'Marketing\nBusiness building\nGame planning\nStory creation\nPresentation\nBudget acquisition and management\nTeam formation\nProject Management\nAdvertising operation', 'Marketing\nBusiness Planning\nPromotion\nGeneral knowledge of programming, design, sound, scenarios, etc. Related to game production', 'Game maker\nGame production company\nIT company', 'Market research\nGame planning\npresentation\nBudget acquisition\nBudget management\nTeam formation\nProject Management', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:07', NULL),
(16, 'Game director', 1, 3, 17, 'The game director is the general manager of the creator team at the game production site.\n\nDozens of specialized creators such as designers, programmers, scenario writers, and sound creators are involved in game production, but as a team organizer, they give instructions to each person in charge and consult on problem solving. However, my main job is to take command so that I can make good works.\nSince the scheduled release time of the game is decided in advance, we will correctly grasp the progress of the project and manage the schedule.\n\nThe game director is a representative position in game development, and it is an important role to make a good game based on ideas.\nIt is also a profession that cultivates a strong mental power as a coordinator in the game industry where unique creators gather.', 'The game director thinks about the finished form of the game to be produced and knows the procedure and method to complete it.\nWe understand the specifications such as pictures and videos used for games, sound effects and music, when they move, and whether to let the user operate them.\nAs the coordinator of the production team, I will take command of the production site while giving instructions to each person in charge and consulting on problem solving.\nWe will accurately grasp the progress of production and manage the schedule so that the game will be completed by the scheduled release date.\nWith interviews with game magazines and public relations for games through videos, prominent game directors are known to users as leaders in production teams.\nIn the case of large-scale games such as popular series from major manufacturers, multiple game directors may be in charge of one game.', 'Presentation\nProject Management\nGame planning\nScenario design\nFunctional design\nOperation of editing software', 'Marketing\nBusiness Planning\nPromotion\nGeneral knowledge of programming, design, sound, scenarios, etc. Related to game production', 'Game maker\nGame production company\nIT company', 'Project meeting\nInstruction\nconsultation\nProgress management', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:16', NULL),
(17, 'Game planner', 4, 5, 26, 'A game planner is a job involved in a wide range of tasks from game planning to completion.\n\nWhat kind of games are popular now and are likely to be popular in the future? We will make a plan by conducting market investment and analysis.\nWe will give a presentation in-house based on the proposal, create a specification when it is decided to actually produce, and prepare for production by deciding a specific schedule and staffing.\nIf you give instructions to programmers and designers based on the specifications, or if you need to make adjustments on the way, the planner will re-establish the direction.\nWhen the prototype is finished, we will do test play and give instructions for fine adjustment and correction, etc. until the game is completed.\n\nIt is no exaggeration to say that the business content covers a wide range of tasks, such as procuring photo materials and checking strategy guides, and saying everything that is necessary to make a game and sell it.\n\nThe main task is to create and execute a concrete project under the direction of the producer or director, and it is an important role for the planner to decide whether or not the game will be interesting.', 'What kind of games are popular now and are likely to be popular in the future? We perform market investment and analysis.\nWhile reflecting the intentions of producers and directors, we will come up with various ideas and create a proposal.\nWe will give a presentation in-house based on the proposal, and when the production is decided, we will create a specification.\nWe will prepare for production by deciding a specific schedule and staffing.\nGive instructions to programmers and designers based on the specifications.\nIf adjustments or corrections are needed on the way, the direction will be summarized again.\nWhen the prototype is completed, we will perform test play and will be involved in the completion of the game, such as giving instructions for fine adjustment and correction.\nIf you need landscape photos for game production, we will procure photos, and if you collaborate with a publisher to make a strategy guide, we will also check the contents. What kind of work you are assigned to depends on the type of game and the fashion, so you need to respond flexibly.\nSome companies treat it as a gateway to game directors.', 'Game planning\nMarketing\nStatistics / analysis\nBusiness building\nPresentation\nCreating specifications\nProject Management\nGame test\n', 'Marketing\nBusiness Planning\nGeneral knowledge of programming, design, sound, scenarios, etc. Related to game production', 'Game maker\nGame production company\nIT company', 'Planning\nCreating specifications\nTest play\nQuality check', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:23', NULL),
(18, 'Game scenario writer', 2, 4, 18, 'A game scenario writer is a job to create scenarios such as scripts, stories, scene developments, and lines according to the content of the game and the persona of the character.\n\nSince it is necessary to write the scenario with the system in mind in line with the planning intention, the director or planner may also serve concurrently.\n\nDue to the spread of social games, many people are migrating from other entertainment fields such as the animation industry, and this is a job that will be attracting attention in the future.', 'Based on the concept of the game, we will create the story development, the character and relationship of the characters that appear, the lines, etc.\nIf there is a change in the specifications, we will make corrections as needed.\nUnlike movies and TV, games branch scenes depending on the player\'s operation and selection, so create a scenario that assumes all the branch patterns.\nDepending on the scene you create, it may be created by a director or planner.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nGame planning power\nScreenplay / Scenario design\nWriting\nDialogue planning\nCharacter setting', 'General knowledge of programming, design, sound, scenarios, etc. related to game production', 'Game maker\nGame production company\nIT company', 'Planning meeting\nStory planning\nCharacter setting\nDialogue devised\nScenario creation\nFix', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:29', NULL),
(19, 'Game programmer', 2, 4, 11, 'A game programmer\'s job is to design logic and algorithms to realize a plan based on a plan and specifications, perform programming, and create a game.\n\nIt also plays an important role in determining whether the game is feasible or impossible at the planning stage.\nWe will create a program so that the game will move as intended, such as character movements, sound settings, and game system construction.\nSome teams check Programming to make sure the program works as intended. The game programmer repeatedly fixes the defects found, and when the final check is completed, the game is finally completed.\n\nIn recent years, with the development of processing technology and networks, the number of games that require complex algorithms and realistic visuals such as 3D and VR is increasing, and game programmers are required to have many skills.', 'Based on the proposal, we will consider whether the ideas considered by the director and planner are feasible from the technical aspect, and design the logic and algorithm and the user flow.\nThe scope of business is to develop a front system that implements the processing of visuals and operations used by users, and a mechanism to process scenarios, calculation logic, algorithms, and so on.\nBased on the specifications and design documents, programming is performed, and while checking for any defects in the program, corrections are made until the defects (commonly known as bug) are resolved.\nIn the case of a large-scale game, it is practically impossible to eliminate all the defects, so determine all the defects and how long it will take to resolve them, consult with the planner and director, and prioritize which defect. I also decide whether to solve it.', 'Programming\nSystem Design\nSystem Test\nGame engine operation\nUse of AI platform\nStatistics / numerical calculation', 'Programming language', 'Game maker\nGame production company\nIT company', 'Planning meeting\ninspection\nSpecification creation\nprogramming\nTest, fix', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Programmer (male)', '24.00', '409.20', 'Starting salary: 240,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 341,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '8,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:34', NULL),
(20, 'Sound creator', 2, 4, 18, 'Sound creator is the job of creating sounds such as BGM and effects for games, animations, and movies.\n\nIn line with the director\'s intention, we will produce not only theme songs and BGM, but also detailed sound effects such as the sound of opening a door and the sound of pressing a button. Voice actors\' voices and performances are recorded in the studio.\n\nSince the impression of the game changes completely with just one BGM or sound effect, it is necessary to make a convincing music after having a close discussion with the site.\nFor famous works, the soundtrack may be sold, and the popularity of the sound creator is often ignited by making the work famous.', 'Since the sound creator is the job of putting sound on a video work, it is not just a job of producing good sound, but also a job of producing sound that matches the image, scene, and character.\nWe will hold in-depth discussions with the site such as the producer and director of the work, and make the production after understanding the production intention of the work.\nIn addition to theme songs and BGM, we also produce detailed sound effects such as the sound of opening a door and the sound of pressing a button.\nVoice actors\' voices and performances are recorded in the studio. We will also witness the recording and make acoustic adjustments such as mixing.', 'Composing and creating sound effects\nMusical instrument performance\nrecording\nMusic Operation of editing software\nMixer operation', 'Knowledge of various sounds and music', 'Game maker\nGame production company\nIT company', 'Planning meeting\nComposition\nrecording\nFix', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:40', NULL),
(21, 'Graphic designer', 2, 4, 18, 'Graphic designers are involved in the promotion and sale of products such as posters and advertising media, books and magazines, product packages and signs, and design flat objects to enhance the visual effect and what you want to convey. It is my job to express.\n\nWe will have a meeting with the client and understand the client\'s intention of what he wants to convey through the production.\nWe collect necessary materials such as having an illustrator draw an illustration or having a cameraman take a picture according to the concept and theme of the design.\nWe process the collected materials with colors and letters to create design drawings.\nAfter checking and modifying the client, we will deliver it to the Printing company when approval is obtained.\n\nOften confused with an illustrator who draws illustrations, graphic designers differ in that they are involved in a wide range of fields from planning to production.', 'We will have a meeting with the client to understand the concept and theme of the product that uses graphics and propose a plan.\nWe collect necessary materials such as drawing illustrations necessary for graphics and taking pictures to create design drawings.\nThere are mainly 2D and 3D in graphic production. In 2D, dots are mainly drawn, and in 3D, polygons are used for expression.\nModeling of characters, parts, backgrounds, textures, shading, etc. are set and completed.', 'Drawing, composition\nColors, color schemes, expressions\nOperation of graphic software (Illustrator, Photoshop)\nProject Management\nOperation of DTP software', 'Design knowledge\n(Composition, layout, colors, fonts)\nPrinting knowledge\nDigital knowledge\nColor coordination', 'Printing company\nAdvertising agency\nDesign Office work place\nthe publisher\nManufacturer Product Development Department\nFreelance', 'Planning meeting\nSample creation\npresentation\nShooting witness\nDesign creation\nFix\nRetouch check\ndelivery of materials', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '7,000～10,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:45', NULL),
(22, 'Animator', 2, 4, 18, 'Animator is the job in charge of drawing, which is the key to animation production.\n\nApproximately 24 pictures are used per second in the animation broadcast on TV, and the animator changes the pose little by little based on the original picture with the original picture man who draws the main picture (original picture). There is a video man who draws additional pictures and makes them appear to move.\n\nOriginal Man thinks about the layout of the cut based on the scenario written by the scriptwriter and the storyboard drawn by the director. Create a rough original picture with movements and backgrounds, and finish the original picture according to the director\'s correction instructions. To create a movie, specify the number of pictures to connect the original pictures and give them movement.\n\nVideo Man draws a video to be inserted between the original images and adjusts it so that it becomes a natural animation.\n\nThe original drawings and videos are drawn by multiple animators, and the animation director directs and fine-tunes the whole to prevent variations in the drawings due to individual habits and abilities.', 'Consider the layout of the cut based on the scenario written by the scriptwriter and the storyboard drawn by the director.\nThere are Original picture man who draws the main picture (original picture) and Video man who draws a picture as an animation based on the original picture.\nThe original picture man creates a rough original picture that depicts the movement and background.\nThe original picture man creates and modifies the original picture according to the director\'s instructions.\nThe original picture man specifies the number of sheets to draw between the original pictures.\nThe video man draws a video to be inserted between the original pictures.\nVideo Man will adjust to a natural animation.', 'Drawing, composition\nColors, color schemes, expressions\nOperation of graphic software\nOperation of animation production software\nShooting, camera work', 'Terminology and tools\nProduction process\nCG and image processing\nArt anatomy\nPsychology', 'Production\nProduction company\nDrawing studio\nFreelance', 'Planning meeting\nOriginal drawing\nVideo creation\nCheck, fix', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 455,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '3,500 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:51', NULL),
(23, 'Manga artist', 2, 4, 18, 'A manga artist is the job of collecting the material of the manga he draws, actually creating the manuscript, and finishing the manga by the deadline.\n\nI am always interested in various things and collect information while collecting manga material.\nWhen we receive a request from the publisher, we will have a meeting with the editor to solidify the idea of ​​the project. Once the plan is decided, the concept of the story is put together in a plot and a name (storyboard) is created. Drafting, pen-filling, solid painting, tone processing, etc. are performed, and the manuscript is finished by the deadline while reflecting the correction instructions from the editor.\n\nThe working hours of cartoonists are not fixed and the image of long working hours is strong, but recently it has become much shorter than before because the parts that were manual work can be operated with a computer, and work introductions and fans on SNS An increasing number of manga artists are promoting their activities through social networking events.', 'I am always interested in various things and collect information while collecting manga material.\nWe will consolidate the idea of manga while having a meeting with the editor of the publisher.\nShe puts the concept of the story into a plot and creates a name (storyboard).\nShe does finishing work such as drafting, pencil case, solid painting and tone processing.\nComplete the manuscript while reflecting the correction instructions from the editor.\nTo become a cartoonist, you can suggest that you bring your manga to a publisher and have it published in a magazine, introduce the manga that you printed and bound yourself to the editor, and publish the manga on SNS and the Internet. There are various ways, such as getting in touch with the editor.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nMarketing\nDrawing, composition\nColors, color schemes, expressions\nCreating a name (frame split, storyboard)\nOperation of manga creation software', 'Design knowledge\n(Composition, layout, colors, fonts)\nDigital knowledge\nHow the human body works\nPsychology', 'Freelance\nAtelier\nAdvertising agency\nThe publisher\nProduction production', 'Looking for material\nPlanning meeting\nPlot creation\nName creation\nName correction\nDraft\nPen holder\nSolid painting\nTone processing\nFinish\ndelivery of materials', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '0.00', '0.00', 'Tens of thousands to hundreds of millions of yen', 'None', 'There are indies etc. and it is impossible to calculate', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 15:55:56', NULL),
(24, 'Illustrator', 2, 4, 18, 'Illustrator creates various illustrations such as game characters, book covers and illustrations, website images and icons.\n\nCreate a sample by handwriting or using graphic software.\n\nA unique touch and sense are required, but the ability to grasp and express the concept of the product using the illustration and the request of the client is required.\n\nRecently, services that use a large number of characters and items such as social games and card games have increased, and the demand for illustrators has increased, and opportunities to introduce works on SNS and sell them by themselves are also increasing.', 'We grasp the concept of products and services that use illustrations and the requests of clients through proposals and hearings, and propose samples based on rough images.\nRough production (sketch before making a single line), line drawing production (making a single line from rough), coloring (painting), finishing based on the instructions submitted by the client before starting production Perform (color and balance adjustment) to complete. In each process, we will confirm the client and proceed with the production while confirming that there is no discrepancy in the contents.\nRegister as a creator and register your work for the purpose of selling with PIxiv or LINE stamps, and carry out sales procedures.\nIntroduce original works and works with permission from the client on SNS etc., perform promotion, and carry out activities to acquire their own fans.', 'Drawing, composition\nColors, color schemes, expressions\nOperation of graphic software (Illustrator, Photoshop)\nIllustration planning and proposal', 'Printing knowledge\nDigital knowledge\nColor coordination', 'Advertising agency\nThe publisher\nDesign Office work place\nPrinting company\nWeb production company', 'Hearing\nSample creation\nIllustration creation\nFix\ndelivery of materials', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Designer (male)', '22.50', '546.00', 'Starting salary: 225,000 ye