(26, 'Copywriter', 4, 5, 26, 'A copywriter is the job of thinking about catchphrases that put products and services on packages, catalogs, posters, etc. so that consumers can catch their eyes, and the text of messages that reflect the image of the company.\n\nCreate multiple samples and select the ones that are primarily sympathetic to the target consumer.\n\nIn order to make a good copy, it is important not only to understand the characteristics of the product or service, but also to understand the corporate philosophy and image, the benefits to consumers and the background of the times, and to make a better copy than the competition. is.\nRecently, services such as AI analyzing these and automatically making copies have appeared.', 'We will accurately grasp the characteristics by interviewing the product plan and the client, actually using the target product or service, and acquiring the user\'s impression by sampling.\nAfter clarifying the target of the target consumer, analyzing the characteristics of the target consumer, behavior / life patterns, trends in the world, and clarifying the points of differentiation from competing products and companies. Create multiple samples and choose the copy that best suits your product and consumer.\nArrange the length and composition of sentences for each medium such as packages, catalogs, posters, newspaper advertisements, websites, etc., and create multiple patterns.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nWriting\nSentence expression\nCopy planning and proposals', 'Knowledge of the products and services that make copies, and the companies and industries\nKnowledge of trends and market needs\nImage of words\nTechnology that logically inspires ideas', 'Advertising agency\nProduction production\nAdvertising department of the manufacturer\nTV station\nRadio stations\nthe publisher\nNewspaper company\nFreelance\nIndependent opening', 'Hearing\nInformation gathering\nPlanning meeting\nTrial production\nsuggestion\nFi