(29, 'Editor', 4, 5, 26, 'An editor is involved in the entire process from planning a book or book to creating a publication.\n\nWe will consider the project together with writers, writers, designers, cameramen, etc., organize the system necessary for realizing the project, check the quality of the created manuscript and product, request correction, and manage until completion.\nIn the case of paper media, we deliver the product to the printing shop, check whether there is a problem with the printed matter, and manage all processes from publication to publication.\n\nRecently, many editors are active not only in paper media but also in web media such as articles on websites, e-mail magazines, and e-books.', 'We will closely communicate with writers and writers to come up with ideas for the project and create the composition of the publication to complete the project.\nIn addition to writers and writers, we organize designers, cameramen, and other systems necessary for realizing the project, set a budget, and manage the completion of the publication.\nWe will make arrangements such as investment and interviews necessary for the publication, confirm the quality of the submitted work from each person in charge, give instructions for correction, and complete the publication.\nIf the publication is on paper, create the manuscript data, deliver it to the print shop, check the final print for problems, and complete it.\nWe arrange the publication and delivery necessary for distributing the publication, and manage the series of processes until it reaches the reader.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nArticle planning\nWriting\nProofreading\nSentence expression\nProject Management', 'Common sense\nCurrent affairs knowledge\nExpertise in the field of planning', 'The publisher\nEditing production\nFreelance', 'Information gathering\nPlanning\nStaff selection\ndirection\nCoverage, simple shooting\nSimple manuscript writing\nLayout\nDraft\nProofreading, review\nS