(39, 'Interior designer', 2, 4, 18, 'An interior designer is the job of designing and designing all kinds of interior spaces, from stores and offices to trains and airplanes.\n\nAfter confirming the request of the client and the usage scene, we will design the interior space and incorporate it into the drawing.\nWe will select a contractor and supervise the construction, such as whether the construction is done according to the drawing or finished according to the image.\nWhen the interior is finished, we will set the furniture and furnishings, and perform after-sales follow-up such as maintenance after delivery.\n\nRecently, it has become easier to create models that express designs in three dimensions with 3D printers, etc., so the content of proposals and the range of activities that can be used are expanding.', 'I usually go to exhibitions to deepen a wide range of knowledge about architecture and interiors, and conduct investigations and tours of magazines, shops and houses.\nIn the design and design of all interior spaces such as stores, offices, trains and airplanes, the client grasps what kind of interior space he wants to make, and based on the request, the color, structure, tone, light, etc. of the interior. We will design the sound and temperature in total and incorporate them into the drawing. We also create simulations and models using 3D perspectives.\nWe may also design and produce interior items such as furniture, curtains and lighting.\nWe will select a contractor to realize the interior space based on the design, and supervise the construction such as whether it is constructed according to the drawing or finished according to the image.\nWe perform after-sales follow-up such as maintenance after delivery, from purchasing furniture and furnishings to setting.', 'Expression technique to sketch ideas\nDrafting (CAD, Illustrator)\nCreate perspective', 'Basic knowledge of space design and art\nKnowledge of basic structure of buildings and building mater