(44, 'First-class architect', 2, 4, 3, 'A first-class architect is a job that supervises the design and construction of buildings such as buildings, commercial theory, and houses based on the Building Law.\n\nWe receive requests from the client and grasp the requests such as budget and image of the building.\nWe make proposals by making drawings or making models in 3D or 2D.\nOnce the design and structure are decided, we will consider safety and earthquake resistance, create detailed design drawings such as structure and equipment, and complete the designed building in cooperation with the construction company and carpenter. Second-class architects cannot design large buildings and commercial facilities, but first-class architects can design and supervise large buildings with a total floor area of 500 m2 or more.\n\nNowadays, we sometimes adopt architectural design and design methods to design not only the building but also the entire area.', 'We will hear your request. Based on the request, we propose ideas and concepts, solidify the image, and create a proposal.\nBased on the proposal, use 3D or 2D CAD to create a drawing or create a model, share the completed image with the client, and finalize the design and design.\nIn addition to design, we also consider safety and earthquake resistance, and create detailed design drawings such as structure, equipment such as electricity and air conditioning.\nBased on the blueprints, we select craftsmen and contractors such as construction and construction companies, carpenters and plasterers, request construction work, complete it while supervising whether it is proceeding according to the blueprints, and hand it over to the customer.\nFirst-class architects are national qualifications that greatly affect the safety of people and the environment, so they participate in regular training sessions and meetings of their affiliations to update their knowledge.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nSpreadsheet softwar