(45, 'Domestic and overseas tour conductors (tour conductor)', 3, 7, 25, 'A tour conductor, commonly known as Tourcon, is a job that accompanies planned trips such as package tours, school trips, and employee trips, and manages the process so that participants can travel with peace of mind.\n\nWe will create processes and bookmarks in advance, arrange transportation, accommodation facilities, restaurants, tourist facilities, etc. according to the process, and manage the progress according to the schedule.\nIn overseas tours, we provide support for immigration and customs declarations, exchange using foreign languages, and provide emergency response in the event of transportation delays, cancellations, sudden illnesses, or theft.\n\nIn particular, it plays an important role in ensuring that group tours proceed safely and as planned, and is an important task that holds the key to the success of the tour that will be remembered by the participants.', 'We grasp the request of the client and the attributes of the participants according to the travel plan, create a process chart and bookmarks in advance, arrange transportation, accommodation facilities, restaurants, tourist facilities, and arrange leisure insurance. And so on.\nFor travel, we manage the process for safely proceeding according to schedule, such as roll calls of participants, confirmation of arrangements for each facility arranged in advance, and guidance.\nIn overseas tours, we provide support for immigration and customs declarations, exchange using foreign languages, and provide emergency response in the event of transportation delays, cancellations, sudden illnesses, or theft.\nWe also understand the local security situation and weather, and give advice so that participants can enjoy the trip safely.\nDuring the tour, we will try to make the trip enjoyable for participants, such as guiding at tourist facilities, guiding meals, and providing meals and topics on the move.', 'Foreign language conversation\nTour guide business\nSafety management\nCrisis avoidance\nPresentation\nDirections', 'Travel Business Law, Terms and Conditions\nKnowledge of local geography, social conditions, history, culture, etc.\nLanguage', 'Tour conductor dispatch company\nTravel agency', 'Meeting\nInformation gathering\nRiding and guidance\n(For overseas) Immigration procedures\nEnsuring safety\nClearing work\nCreating a report', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Train conductor (male)', '27.80', '452.40', 'Starting salary: 278,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 377,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '15,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:00:17', NULL),
(46, 'Construction site supervision', 5, 1, 6, 'The construction site supervisor is the person in charge of the construction site, and is responsible for managing costs, processes, quality, and safety.\n\nWe will carry out all necessary management to carry out the construction work as planned. At the time of construction, we will also hold briefing sessions and respond to inquiries to local residents so that the construction will proceed smoothly.\n\nAs the construction site grows larger, multiple contractors and workers come and go, so the role of the site supervisor who controls the site becomes important.\n\nNormally, the site supervisor works as an employee of a construction company, but recently, more and more people have specialized knowledge and skills such as qualifications such as first-class architect and first-class construction management engineer and work freelance.', 'We will consider the construction order, process, material transportation, work flow line, etc. and create a construction plan.\nWe manage costs so that construction can proceed according to budget, such as cost calculation of labor costs and material costs, selection of contractors and materials, ordering, monthly cost calculation, etc.\nWe will hold briefing sessions for local residents during construction and make adjustments such as responding to inquiries so as not to inconvenience the residents around the construction site.\nSince many contractors go in and out of the construction site for civil engineering work, construction work, and housing construction, we will manage the process while checking and adjusting whether the work is proceeding according to the schedule and whether it is behind schedule. ..\nWe will prepare the environment so that the materials can be used under the optimum conditions, provide technical guidance to workers, and perform quality control so that the strength and density meet the specified values.\nTo prevent accidents at construction sites, we will install fire extinguishing equipment, install safety equipment such as handrails in dangerous places, and perform safety management such as daily inspections and talking with workers.', 'Project Management\nPlan preparation\nDesign document creation\nQuality management\nOperation of construction management software', 'Architecture\nCivil engineering\nMaterial\nConstruction method\nConstruction Business Act\nAccounting', 'Construction shop\nDesign Office work place\nHouse maker\nreal-estate company', 'Contractor meeting\nExamination and creation of construction plans\nOrdering of materials and vendors\nDrawing check\nRecord\nProgress, process control\nSafety management\nBudget management', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Carpenter (male)', '19.60', '301.20', 'Starting salary: 196,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 251,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '560,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 8, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:00:23', NULL),
(47, 'Surveyor', 5, 1, 4, 'A surveyor is a job to accurately reduce the position and shape of land in building work.\n\nIn order to carry out efficient and accurate surveying, we will make a work plan, surveying plan, etc. in advance.\nA team of 2 to 5 people will conduct a survey and create drawings using surveying software.\nIt is also the job of the surveyor to check that the structure actually constructed is in the correct location.\n\nSurveying of places that were previously difficult to survey can now be done by using a drone or 3D laser scanner.', 'In order to carry out efficient and accurate surveying, we will make a work plan, surveying plan, etc. in advance.\nIn the outside business, a team of 2 to 5 people surveys the planned construction site using specialized equipment and surveying techniques.\nIn the internal business, we procure budget pipes and equipment related to surveying, and create drawings using surveying software based on the surveyed data.\nCheck if the structure actually constructed is in the correct location.', 'Surveying technology\nMaking the plan\nSurvey planning\nSurvey data analysis\nDrone maneuver\nOperation of surveying software\nReading comprehension of topographic maps', 'Surveying regulations, international treaties\nReference point survey\nTopographic survey\nPhotogrammetry\nMap editing\nApplied surveying\nTraverse survey\nPan-Earth Positioning System Survey\nLeveling\nGeographic information system', 'Surveying Office work office\nConsultant company\nAerial survey company\nCivil engineering, construction, real estate industry\nCompanies creating maps\nGeospatial Information Authority of Japan\nMinistry of Land, Infrastructure, Transport and Tourism\nMinistry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries\nCivil engineering section of each prefecture', 'Planning a survey plan\nVisit to the site\nSurveying\nMaking the plan\nExplanation, delivery', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Surveyor (male)', '22.00', '463.20', 'Starting salary: 220,000 yen (Company siz