(48, 'Electrical worker', 5, 1, 6, 'An electrician is the job of constructing and maintaining all the electrical equipment in the world.\n\nThere are roughly two types of electrical work: railway electrical work and building electrical work. Railroad electrical work involves the construction and maintenance of all electrical equipment required for railways, and building electrical work includes the installation of electrical equipment for new construction and existing buildings. Perform maintenance and inspection.\n\nIn recent years, there are more things that cannot be realized without electrical work, such as switching to natural energy such as environmentally friendly solar power generation and increasing demand for electrical energy due to industrial development, and the demand for electricians is also increasing. doing.', 'There are roughly two types: railway electrical work and building electrical work.\nRailroad electrical work includes overhead lines that send electricity to trains, signal systems that support safe operation, railroad crossings, station lighting and communication equipment, and power plants and substations that supply power.\nFor new construction electrical work, electrical wiring inside the building and installation work of switchboards and various electrical equipment are performed.\nFor construction electrical work on existing buildings, we will maintain and inspect the installed electrical equipment, and add new wiring and electrical equipment.\nElectricians include Type 1 electricians and Type 2 electricians.\nType 1 electricians can perform electrical work on private electric facilities with a maximum power of less than 500KW, including the range of type 2.\nType 2 electricians can perform electrical work on general electric facilities. Electric facilities for general use are those that receive low-voltage power in general houses and shops, and are relatively safe electric facilities that receive power by dropping it to 600V or less with a transformer from a utility pole on a road or the like.', 'Reading and creating construction drawings and wiring diagrams\nWiring work\nInfrastructure creation\nConstruction management', 'Electrical theory\nElectrical measurement\nElectrical equipment\nElectrical material\nPower transmission and distribution\nElectrical regulations\nDrafting (including wiring diagram)', 'Electrical work company\nConstruction / construction company\nHome appliance maker', 'Check the process chart\nVisit to the site\nCheck the drawing\nConstruction\nConfirmation\nEnergized\nSupport for other sites\nPreparation for the next day', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Electrician (male)', '25.60', '451.20', 'Starting salary: 256,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 376,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '302,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:00:35', NULL),
(49, 'Civil engineering worker', 5, 1, 6, 'Civil engineering workers are responsible for transporting luggage, mixing concrete with a mixer, and driving heavy machinery at construction sites.\n\nIn public works, in addition to facilities such as gas, water, and electricity necessary for living infrastructure, large rivers and dams are constructed, and in construction, residential land, condominiums, and buildings are constructed.\n\nThere is also work to perform restoration work such as landslides and floods at disaster sites.\n\nAt work sites where only men used to be, the number of civil engineering girls (commonly known as Dobojo) is gradually increasing due to the reduction of physical burden due to division of labor and the improvement of the work environment.', 'The earthwork work is in charge of hard work such as transporting luggage and stirring to mix and generate concrete with a mixer and auxiliary work, and while gaining experience, acquire the license necessary for operating heavy machinery and become a mechanical earthworker. I will expand the width of.\nFor large-scale construction and public works, we will bury roads, rivers, dams, bridges, buildings, gas, water, electricity, etc. underground.\nIn the construction work, we will construct residential land, condominiums and buildings, reorganize the land, reorganize the cultivated land in rice fields and fields, and improve irrigation canals and drainage canals.\nIn disaster recovery, we will repair, reinforce, and demolish disaster sites such as landslides and floods.', 'Vehicle driving technique\nHeavy equipment operation technology\nCivil engineering construction technology\nSurveying technology', 'Safety management\nCivil engineering design\nCivil engineering method', 'Civil engineering company\nConstruction company', 'Site visit\nRoad and land maintenance\nOperation of heavy machinery\nDriving a vehicle', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Earthwork (male)', '24.70', '456.00', 'Starting salary: 247,000 yen (Company size