(50, 'Real estate appraiser', 5, 1, 6, 'Real estate Appraisal is a job to determine the economic value of real estate such as land and buildings and calculate the price.\n\nThe value of the real estate is examined from information such as the register and geology and land use plans. In addition, we provide consulting on the management and utilization of real estate entrusted to us by our clients. We may also undertake operations from public institutions, appraisal of personal inheritance tax and property tax, and asset valuation of companies.\n\nAmong the lawyers, certified accountants, and real estate appraisal qualifications, which are called the three major national qualifications of liberal arts, the balance between supply and demand is the best, and the number of jobs is increasing.', 'You can check the registered information about real estate such as the requested land and building, and investigate the City Planning Act, Building Standards Act, National Land Use Planning Act, etc. at the municipal office.\nWe will conduct an Appraisal evaluation of the real estate by conducting a local investment, investigating whether the boundary with the adjacent land matches the registered information, investigating the adjacency of the road, and asking the opinion of a local real estate agent.\nWe provide consulting on the management of real estate entrusted to us by the client and how to utilize the real estate.\nWe perform land price announcements, prefectural land price investigations, and appraisal evaluations of inheritance tax and property tax conducted by the national and prefectural governments.\nWe also acquire public land, evaluate fixed assets in court, and evaluate corporate assets.\nSince the Appraisal amount fluctuates depending on the land usage situation, we predict future usage from our own information network and political economy news.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nInvestigation\nLand price forecast', 'Land Basic Law\nAct on Real Es