(51, 'Environmental consultant', 5, 1, 6, 'An environmental consultant is the job of investigating and predicting the social environment and natural environment during construction, and planning and planning environmental conservation measures that minimize the impact.\n\nIn addition, we provide investigations and improvement guidance to see if they meet the standards of laws and regulations, environmental policies of local governments and general companies, planning proposals for environmental businesses, and consultation services for local residents.\n\nIn recent years, regulations and awareness of environmental protection, such as carbon offsetting, which regulates carbon dioxide emissions, have been increasing on a global scale. Especially in large-scale development, it will play an important role in leaving a better environment in the future.', 'At the time of construction, we carry out a wide range of environmental investigations such as the natural environment and ecosystems of animals and plants, conduct environmental assessments to investigate, predict and evaluate the impact on the environment, and create an environmental report.\nWe calculate costs for environmental conservation in urban and regional development, propose improvement measures to avoid environmental destruction, and provide improvement guidance to developers.\nWe provide planning proposals for local governments\' environmental policies, advice on the operation of accreditation such as the ISO certification system, and consultation services for local residents.\nWe provide guidance on environmental conservation activities promoted by general companies as CSR activities (corporate social responsibility) and support for acquiring international standards related to the environment.', 'Environmental Investigation\nEnvironmental protection\nFinding and solving problems\nPresentation\nProject Management\nCommunication with local residents', 'Physics\nbiology\nChemistry\nEarth, space science\nEnvironmental science\nEnergy and resource engineering', 'Laboratory\nConsulting company\nResearch company', 'Assessment\nPreparation of environmental report\nCost calculation\nProposal of improvement measures\nImprovement guidance\nConsultation of local residents\nInternational standard acquisition support\nPlanning recommendations for local government environmental policies', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Engineer (male)', '25.80', '502.80', 'Starting salary: 258,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 419,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 8, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:02:37', NULL),
(52, 'Farmer', 5, 1, 4, 'A farmer is the job of growing and shipping edible rice and vegetables, ornamental flowers and herbs.\n\nIn addition to the production of agricultural products, we also carry out a wide range of operations from production to sales, such as agricultural machine operation training, sales and sales operations. In addition, we will summarize and record the status of daily shipments and activities, and research more delicious plants, breeding and cultivation methods so that stable harvesting can be achieved. Production methods are also diversifying, such as pesticide-reduced cultivation, pesticide-free cultivation, and organic cultivation.\n\nRecently, there has been an active movement to secure human resources by building a stable management base as an agricultural corporation.', 'We make soil for growing crops, such as adding fertilizer to agricultural land such as rice fields and fields and cultivating soil with a tractor.\nWe will prepare by collecting information on agricultural machinery, training in operation, maintenance, etc. on a daily basis according to the crops to be cultivated.\nWe plant and sow rice by hand or using a rice transplanter or planter, and when the plants are fully grown, we harvest them in consideration of the shipping time.\nWe manage rice fields and fields by adding fertilizer, removing weeds, and exterminating pests.\nWe sort by grade according to the size and color gloss of the plants, pack them in bags and boxes, and carry out shipping work such as bringing them to the agricultural cooperative\'s collection point, supermarket collection and delivery office, and direct sales office.\nWe summarize and record the status of daily shipments and activities, improve varieties, research cultivation methods, and exchange information between farmers so that more delicious plants can be harvested in a stable manner.\nWe will take measures and collect information in case of natural disasters caused by changes in weather and climate, and damage from birds and animals.', 'Basic knowledge about seeds and fertilizers\nOperation of agricultural equipment such as rice transplanters and agricultural machines\nLearning how to grow, manage and separate plants\nOffice work such as accounting and sales management', 'Agriculture\nAgricultural production\nAgricultural mechanics\nAgricultural management\nAgricultural chemistry\nAgricultural engineering\nAgricultural economics\nCultivation management method\nPest control\nIntroduction to Soil Fertilizer\nLife agriculture\nAgricultural business\nAccounting, accounting', 'Farmer\nAgricultural sector of a company', 'Making soil\nRice planting / seed planting\nDaily care\nHarvest\nShipping\nResearch on breeding, etc.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Natural science researcher (male)', '25.60', '573.60', 'Starting salary: 256,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 478,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '2,200,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:02:44', NULL),
(53, 'Beekeeper', 5, 1, 4, 'A beekeeper is the job of raising bees and collecting bee nectar.\n\nNectars are set up within the habitat of bees to control hygiene and temperature, as well as to manage the health of bees, grow them, and collect nectar.\n\nIn addition to collecting honey, we also sell too many bees and rent bees for pollination to farmers.\n\nBees have a great influence on the pollination of crops, and the shortage of bees has become a problem worldwide since the mid-2000s. There are Japanese honeybees, and we often use honeybees, which have a large amount of nectar.', 'In addition to creating and repairing nest boxes, controlling hygiene and temperature, we also manage the health of honeybees and take measures against the natural enemy wasps.\nFor honey collection, smoke is generated with a smoker to suppress the behavior of bees, and the nest frame is removed from the nest box and placed in a centrifuge to extract honey.\nWe sell too many bees and rent bees for pollination to farmers.\nIn some cases, honey is processed and sold by itself.', 'Birdhouse temperature control and hygiene control\nBee health care\nHoney collection\nTasting\nOffice work such as accounting and sales management', 'Ecology\nBee disease\nBeekeeping\nFlower type\nHoney type\nThe effect of honey', 'Beekeeper\nApiary', 'Bee health care\nBirdhouse management\nInsulation management\nMeasures against wasps\nWork to collect honey', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Natural science researcher (male)', '25.60', '573.60', 'Starting salary: 256,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 478,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '5,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:02:50', NULL),
(54, 'Dairy farmer', 5, 1, 4, 'Dairy workers are a profession that mainly raises dairy cows and produces raw milk, which is the raw material for dairy products.\n\nOur daily routine is to raise dairy cows, clean and manage the barn, milk and ship. In addition, we grow pasture by ourselves and assist in childbirth.\nThere are also dairy farmers who process their own milk to make dairy products such as butter and cheese.\n\nIf milking is infrequent, you will not be able to rest for a day because you will end up with a disease called mastitis, in which bacteria invade the nipples of cows and lead to death.\nThe price of dairy cows is soaring and it is important to give birth safely, and the number of dairy farmers who have a 24-hour internet monitoring system is increasing.', 'As a daily routine, we clean the barn, feed, care for the cows, and milk.\nMaintenance such as disinfection of milking equipment, sterilization, disinfection, and drying of dairy cow nipples is performed, and in order to keep the cow in a healthy condition, sleeping straw that serves as a bed for cows is laid and dirty sleeping straw is cleaned up. Create a clean living environment.\nBy brushing the cow\'s hair, it relieves the stress of the cow and also removes feed, straw, manure, etc. that are entwined with the hair to prevent accidents where foreign substances are mixed in during milking.\nCultivate and preserve the grass that serves as feed, mix corn to make feed, and feed it in two separate doses, morning and evening.\nWe perform natural mating and artificial insemination for breeding, manage and observe the progress, and help cattle if they have a difficult birth at the time of delivery.\nIn some cases, the collected milk is processed to make dairy products such as butter and cheese.\nSome dairy farmers produce raw goat milk.', 'Hygiene management of barns, etc.\nDairy cow health care\nMilking\nCultivation of pasture\nFeed making', 'Animal Science\nBreeding management\nHygiene management\nBreeding theory, technology\nBreeding management theory\nCultivation of forage crops\nFeed storage technology\nDairy business management technology\nDairy facility management\nMachine operation and management', 'Dairy farmer', 'Cleaning\nFeeding\nPreparing for sleeping straw\nMilking\nHealth care\nPasture cultivation\nArtificial insemination\nChildbirth assistance', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Natural science researcher (male)', '25.60', '573.60', 'Starting salary: 256,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 478,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', '15,700 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:02:57', NULL),
(55, 'Forestry engineer', 5, 1, 4, 'A forestry technician is the job of planning and planning forest management methods and creating plans for forestry.\n\nWe go to forestry sites and forest roads to conduct on-site investigations, formulate forest management and management plans, and supervise and instruct on-site implementation of the plans.\n\nThe qualification of a forestry technician is a private qualification, but it requires deep knowledge and experience in forests, such as requiring up to 14 years of work experience depending on the educational background.\nThe woody biomass business, which promotes the reuse of forestry resources, is attracting attention, and the opportunities for forestry engineers to play an active role are expanding.', 'We go to forests and forest roads to conduct on-site investigations and collect data such as surveying and sampling.\nDevelop a concrete plan and method for forest management and management, and compile it as a plan.\nIn implementing the plan, we will go to the work site, supervise and instruct forestry workers, and provide dissemination guidance to forest owners.\nWe patrol the forests in the area in charge to check the growth status and the presence of abnormalities, and maintain and manage forest resources.\nWe regularly acquire the latest information on forests and forestry, and participate in learning and seminars on acquiring and renewing qualifications.', 'Formulation of forest management plan\nForest pricing\nForest management and monitoring\nPresentation\nFinding and solving problems\nProject Management', 'Forestry management\nForestry machinery\nForest civil engineering\nForest evaluation\nForest environment\nForest products\nForest comprehensive management\nWork road construction', 'Paper and pulp companies\nHousing industry\nTrading company\nForestry company\nEnvironmental assessment company\nResearch Institute\nNational public park\nGovernment offices, local governments', 'Survey, surveying\nSampling\nCreatio