(60, 'Pharmaceutical developer', 5, 1, 2, 'A drug developer is the job of conducting research and clinical trials necessary for new drug development.\n\nWe carry out basic research such as chemical research and biological research, conduct clinical trials by administering to animals and actually humans, and if the efficacy and safety are confirmed, we will even apply for a new drug.\nIn addition, in order to reflect the voices of patients and the needs of medical institutions in the development and improvement of drugs, we will work closely with other departments to develop drugs.\n\nIt is said that the development of new drugs takes a long development period of about 10 years or more and costs 20 to 30 billion yen, and the financial burden is heavy, so generic drugs, which are generic drugs, are increasing.', 'In research on new drug development, we conduct basic research to investigate substances and components from biological research such as plants and animals and chemical research such as microorganisms and chemical substances, and to create new substances and components by combining them.\nWe will conduct preclinical (animal experiments) to investigate the safety and efficacy of substances using animals and cultured cells, and conduct clinical trials to confirm the efficacy and safety by administering to humans.\nWe will respond to applications such as applying to the Pharmaceuticals and Medical Devices Agency (PMDA) for new drugs that have been confirmed to be effective and safe.\nIn order to reflect the voices of patients and the needs of medical institutions in the development and improvement of medicines, we will work closely with other departments to develop medicines.', 'Clinical trial\nDrug discovery\nOperation of experimental equipment\nCommunication\nPlanning and management\nStatistics and calculations', 'Biology\nLife science\nBasic medicine\nChemistry\nPharmaceuticals\nMedical pharmacy\nHygiene pharmacy\nBioinformatics\nPharmaceutical affairs regula