(61, 'Car engineer', 5, 1, 1, 'An automobile engineer is a job of researching and developing automobile bodies and parts with a car maker.\n\nFor automobiles, there are engineers for each part such as body, chassis, interior, engine drive system, and undercarriage, and each of them repeats various tests and evaluations to make improvements, and when the prototype is completed, planning the manufacturing process and designing and manufacturing equipment. And prepare for production.\n\nCurrently, in the automobile market, the development of next-generation automobiles such as electric vehicles and self-driving cars is underway, and not only Car makers but also new companies such as electric manufacturers and IT companies are participating in these markets.', 'Once the car is planned and designed, it will be developed by a team of parts such as body, chassis, interior, engine drive train, and suspension.\nWe research trends and needs in the automobile market, constantly research and develop from design studies to body weight reduction, engine output increase, fuel efficiency reduction, etc., and continue for the next model change even after the product is completed. We will carry out research and development.\nProduct designers design with CAD in consideration of designability, productivity, strength, etc., and design by simulating vehicle strength, performance, etc. with a computer.\nIn the development process, we make full-scale prototypes of bodies and parts, repeat various tests and evaluations, and make improvements to complete the prototype.\nWe prepare for production by designing and manufacturing process planning, equipment design and manufacturing of press dies, welding lines, assembly lines, painting lines, etc. according to production.', 'Research and Development\nDesign, drafting\nOperation of design software\nCommunication\nProject Management', 'Automotive engineering\nSystem control engineering\nthermodynamics\nFluid mechanics\nmechanical engineering\nElectrical and electronic engineering\nEnvironmental protection\nSafety management\nMaterial', 'Car maker', 'Planning, planning\nDesign\nDesign\nTrial production\nExperiment\nEvaluation\nPreparation for production', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Car assembler (male)', '28.70', '450.00', 'Starting salary: 287,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 375,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:03:56', NULL),
(62, 'Printing engineer', 5, 1, 4, 'A printing engineer is the job of operating a printing machine to manufacture printed matter based on instructions at a printing shop.\n\nSkilled skills are required for printing technology, and the amount of ink is adjusted according to the quality of the paper, taking into consideration the characteristics of the printing machine and the temperature and humidity of the factory, to produce beautiful printed matter.\n\nWith the recent digitization by IT, the demand for technology to operate printing machines is occurring, but the search for new businesses such as new product development utilizing printing and processing technology and fusion with IT is expanding. ..', 'We operate the printing machine to print based on the contents instructed according to the design of posters, catalogs, magazines, etc.\nBased on our printing experience, we understand the characteristics of printing machines, consider changes in temperature and humidity in the factory due to the seasons and weather, adjust the amount of ink according to the quality of the paper, and finish beautiful printed matter.\nAfter printing, the printed matter may be cut with a cutting machine, etc., or special decoration or processing such as die cutting may be performed.\nAfter printing and processing, we will clean, maintain and maintain the printing press for the production of the next printed matter.', 'Operation of printing machine\nColor management\nPrinting machine maintenance', 'Paper type and characteristics\nInk types and characteristics', 'Printing company', 'Planning meeting\nPrinting plan review and planning\nPaper selection\nAdjusting the amount of ink\nMachine operation\nInspection\nPacking\nCleaning\nMachine maintenance', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Offset printer (male)', '25.40', '435.60', 'Starting salary: 254,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 363,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2