(63, 'CAD operator', 5, 1, 5, 'A CAD operator is a job to create drawings and 3D data using drawing support software called CAD (Computer Aided Design).\n\nSince it is a job that specializes in CAD operations, I input it into CAD according to the instructions of the designer or designer, and correct the data if there is a change. Manage the created drafting data so that you can check and share it at any time.\n\nCAD has a strong image of being used in industrial products such as automobiles and communication equipment in addition to architecture, but it is widely used in furniture and apparel design.\nIn recent years, automation by AI has progressed, and at the same time as the efficiency of CAD operators has improved, the number of jobs is decreasing, which is a valuable job.', 'It is a job that specializes in CAD operations, and according to the instructions of designers and designers, CAD is used to modify, adjust, and create drawings.\nYou can perform various CAD operations such as drawing in 2D with 2D CAD, drawing a solid in 3D with 3D CAD, and arranging it in a virtual space.\nWe will work closely with the designer to respond to requests for corrections and adjustments and complete the drawing.', 'PC operation\nOperation of CAD software\nCommunication\nReading development drawings and construction drawings', 'Computer system\nBasic knowledge of networks\nInformation security and intellectual property\nDrafting\nShape\nBasic knowledge of 3D CAD', 'Construction company\nCivil Engineering Office work place\nDesign Office work place\nCar maker\nApparel company\nElectronics company\nMachine maker', 'Receive instructions from designers and designers\nMaking the plan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Computer operator (male)', '22.40', '444.00', 'Starting salary: 224,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 370,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:04:12', NULL),
(64, 'Scientific investigation researcher', 8, 2, 8, 'Forensic researchers are jobs that appraisal evidence and conduct criminal investigations in order to scientifically elucidate and prove crimes.\n\nAt the Scientific Investigation Research Institute established at the Prefectural Police Headquarters, forensic science, chemistry, engineering / physics, documents, psychology, field science, etc. are divided into specialized fields to conduct forensic investigations.\n\nIn today\'s diversified crime world, the physical evidence left at the scene of an incident or accident can be a clue to the truth and arrest of the criminal, and the Appraisal result is important evidence for the trial.\nRecently, there are many TV dramas with the theme of forensics researchers, and you can see its importance.', 'Forensic science has specialized fields such as forensic medicine, chemistry, engineering / physics, documents, psychology, and field science, and we work at the forensic science research institute established at the prefectural police headquarters.\nIn the forensic field, blood, body fluids, bones, skin, etc. are inspected and applied, and personal identification is performed by blood type and DNA type Appraisal.\nIn the field of chemistry, we inspect narcotics, poisonous and deleterious substances, blood alcohol, etc., and identify fine fiber pieces, paints, gunpowder, etc.\nIn the engineering and physics fields, we will elucidate the causes of fires, collapse of mechanical structures, traffic accidents, etc., and perform performance inspections and identification of firearms and bullets.\nIn the document field, we appraisal documents such as handwriting, imprints, printed matter, counterfeit currency, and passports.\nThe field of psychology conducts polygraph tests and criminal psychology research that appraisal the credibility of statements.\nIn the field of field science, when an incident occurs, we will be dispatched to the field and immediately perform a simple appraisal.', 'Fingerprint appraisal\nIrony document examination\nVoiceprint / voice appraisal\nDNA test\nImage appraisal\nTraffic accident appraisal\nFire appraisal', 'Forensic science\nScience\nPhysics\nForensic medicine\nPsychology\nBiochemistry\nMolecular biology\nChemistry\nPharmacy\nChemical engineering', 'Scientific Investigation Institute\nNational Research Institute of Police Science', 'Fingerprint appraisal\nIrony document examination\nVoiceprint / voice appraisal\nDNA test\nImage appraisal\nTraffic accident appraisal\nFire appraisal', 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Chemical analyst (male)', '24.00', '468.00', 'Starting salary: 240,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 390,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'None', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 6, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:04:18', NULL),
(65, 'Day trader', 6, 6, 21, 'A day trader is a job that makes a profit by repeatedly buying and selling financial products such as stocks and Forex during the day.\n\nWe research the movements of the world, financial statements and press releases of companies, predict stock fluctuations, analyze charts from past stock price movements, and repeatedly buy and sell mainly on the Internet.\nTrading is possible from 9:00 to 11:00 and 12:30 to 15:00 on weekdays when the stock market is open, and since the FX market is open 24 hours a day excluding Saturdays and Sundays, it is possible to trade all day long. I can do it.\n\nIn recent years, the number of day traders is increasing, regardless of whether they are full-time or side businesses, because high-speed Internet and smartphones have become widespread, and securities companies have reduced fees and provided software necessary for transactions free of charge.', 'We research the latest information on the world such as newspapers, Internet news, corporate financial statements and press releases, predict stock fluctuations, and analyze charts from past stock price movements.\nThe stock market is open only for 2 hours in the morning from 9:00 to 11:00 and about 2 hours and 30 minutes in the afternoon from 12:30 to 15:00, so it is within that time. Make a transaction.\nThe Forex market is open 24 hours a day, excluding weekends, so you can trade all day long.\nUsing chart software that can grasp stock price fluctuations in real time in the Internet environment, you can predict stock price fluctuations and repeat buying and selling while looking at an index called a chart.\nYou can make a profit by buying stocks whose prices are likely to rise while they are cheap, and selling them when they are high.', 'Trade', 'Stock\nEconomy\nFinance', 'One\'s home\nPersonal Office work place', 'Information gathering\nAnalysis\nBuying and selling', 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '0.00', '0.00', '', 'Open an account at a securities company', 'Not clear'