(69, 'Accounting', 7, 8, 29, 'Accounting is the job of recording and managing the inflows and outflows of money in a company or organization.\n\nUse accounting software and spreadsheet software on your computer to calculate and manage income and expenditure, bank deposits, salaries, insurance, taxes, etc. We are also involved in the preparation of financial statements, and perform monthly and annual financial statement operations.\nWe manage the credit of our business partners and create and improve accounting rules for the entire company.\n\nIt is a job that allows you to know the management situation, such as whether the company is making a profit, and depending on the size of the company, the distance from the management is short and it becomes a staff position.', 'Use accounting software and spreadsheet software to record and manage daily deposits and withdrawals such as small-lot settlement, deposit management, sales / payment confirmation, and expense settlement.\nWe create analysis data such as income and expenditure transitions and ratios from the flow of money, and share and report to related business divisions.\nAs a settlement-related business, we create financial statements such as financial statements and securities reports.\nShare accounting and analysis data with tax accountants and certified accountants to process journal entries and create monthly financial statements.\nIt manages the credit examination of business partners and the transaction status and payment status.\nWe create and improve accounting rules for the entire company, such as expense application and order management, as well as within the department.\nWe negotiate with financial institutions such as banks regarding financing.', 'Document creation / editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nJournal and accounting processing\nAccounting software operation\nAccounting, payroll', 'Tax, accounting and management laws\nDaily, monthly and annual financial statements\nCorporate tax\nCorporate residence tax