(73, 'Wine sommelier', 7, 8, 28, 'A wine sommelier is a job to properly manage wine and customer service related to wine at restaurants and wine stores.\n\nWe understand customers\' tastes, budgets, foods to be eaten, etc., select the best wine, and propose and provide it.\nIn addition to wine, we also learn and acquire knowledge about cooking and ingredients, geography and history of production areas, purchase and manage all beverages handled at stores, and select and manage the glasses to be provided.\n\nIn major wine countries such as France and Italy, sommeliers are required to have a high level of education and are national qualifications.', 'We collect information on wines from around the world on a daily basis, participate in tasting sessions, and conduct research.\nYou will learn information and research on other beverages that you eat and drink with wine, food and ingredients, and other information such as the geography and history of the wine producing area.\nAt restaurants and other shops, wine that matches the food is selected and procured in advance, and temperature and humidity are controlled.\nWe also supervise the dishes and ingredients to be served, select and procure glasses for each wine.\nIn customer service such as restaurants and wine stores, we grasp the food, taste, budget, etc. that the customer eats, select the best wine, and introduce and provide it.\nSince there are many wines produced overseas, we sometimes use foreign languages ​​for wine selection and purchasing, so we also learn languages.\nWhen it comes to popular sommeliers, we sometimes have fans, such as supervising multiple stores and writing books, so we regularly hold seminars and events on how to choose wine.', 'Tasting\nBusiness manner\nTable manners\nProposal power', 'Language\nExtensive knowledge of wine\nCooking knowledge', 'French restaurant\nItalian restaurant\nHotel restaurant\nWine bar', 'Customer service\nHearing about tastes and dishes\nWine suggestions and introduct