(74, 'Patissier', 8, 2, 33, 'Pastry chef has the meaning of a craftsman who makes sweets and is a job to make various Western confectionery such as cakes and cookies.\n\nWe belong to pastry shops, restaurants, hotel cafes, etc. and manufacture pastry. Popular pastry chefs supervise owners of multiple stores, restaurant desserts, and collaborative products with confectionery makers. In addition to making sweets, we may also participate in various contests and teach lectures.\n\nAn increasing number of people have practiced in Europe, the home of Western confectionery, and have returned to Japan to become popular pastry chefs.', 'As a confectionery craftsman, I make various Western confectioneries such as cakes, cookies, chocolates, and ice cream.\nWe conduct daily research on making sweets, such as creating and improving product recipes, examining new sweets, and making prototypes.\nIf you belong to a pastry shop, hotel, or restaurant that has multiple stores, multiple pastry chefs will belong to you, and you will work on each process such as preparation, manufacturing, and finishing.\nIn the case of a specialty store that sells over-the-counter, we prepare for opening, display the finished sweets in a showcase, and sell to customers. After the store is closed, we will clean the inside of the store and prepare for the next day\'s business.\nIn addition to making sweets, we may also participate in various contests and teach lectures.\nI may also be in charge of purchasing raw materials for sweets, production control, and inventory control.', 'Making the groundwork\nBaked and chilled\nNappe\nAperture\nDecoration\nDesign\nHygiene management\nOperation of dedicated equipment', 'Material\nRuset (recipe)', 'Western confectionery specialty store\nPastry maker\nHotel\nWedding hall\nRestaurant\nPastry class', 'Making sweets\nProduct development\nCleaning\nMaterial ordering and management\nTool management\nPackaging of sweets\nCustomer service', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bread / Western co