(75, 'Cooks', 8, 2, 33, 'A cook is a job that involves cooking, nutritional management, and hygiene management at restaurants, accommodation facilities, and medical institutions.\n\nWe make various dishes according to the management and the store or facility to which we belong. We purchase and manage ingredients according to the recipes in the store, and also create new recipes. In addition, we always maintain a hygienic environment by cleaning the equipment.\n\nRecently, due to the popularity of recipe books and video sites, not only stores and facilities, but also recipe provision and video appearances are increasing the places where cooks can play an active role.', 'Depending on the place to which you belong, such as restaurants, accommodation facilities, and medical institutions, you can make use of cooking techniques to cook Japanese, Western, Chinese, and other dishes according to the recipe.\nWe purchase ingredients, manage inventory, and manage storage such as freshness and expiration date.\nIn order to renew the menu, we plan new menus, make prototypes, and develop recipes.\nWe always maintain a hygienic environment by cleaning facilities and equipment.\nAt school and hospital lunch facilities, menus are decided and cooked under the nutritional guidance of a dietitian.\nAt stores with multiple stores or stores with multiple cooks, there may be underlaying, etc., and we also provide education and guidance for newcomers.', 'Preparation\nKitchen knife\nHeating cooling\nSeasoning\nArrangement\nFood management technology\nHygiene management\nStore management', 'Introduction to culture\nHygiene regulations\nPublic health\nNutrition\nFood science\nFood hygiene\nCooking theory', 'Restaurant\nHotel\nWedding hall\nFood companies\nCatering service\nSide dish specialty store\nSchool lunch room, school cafeteria\nCorporate employee cafeteria\nKitchens such as hospitals and welfare facilities', 'Preparation\nCooking\nArrangement\nClean up and clean\nHygiene management\nM