(77, 'Prosecutor', 7, 8, 22, 'A public prosecutor belongs to three legal professionals (judge, public prosecutor, lawyer) and has the authority to prosecute a crime. He is in charge of judging prosecution and directing and supervising executions.\n\nHe investigates and examines the case and decides whether to prosecute or not. If the suspect needs to be prosecuted, he will be prosecuted, and the court will make an opening statement, provide evidence, summon witnesses, and seek a sentence. Once convicted, he directs and oversees law enforcement.\n\nIn today\'s internationalized world, transnational crimes are on the rise. Therefore, prosecutors are required to have the ability to tackle international crimes such as language understanding.', 'We will investigate and examine the cases that have been prosecuted or accused directly to the police or the public prosecutor, and decide whether to prosecute or not.\nWitness the trial that decided to prosecute, submit evidence to the court, cross-examine witnesses, prove that the accused committed a crime, and file a criminal prosecution. We may also appeal (appeal) to the court.\nOnce found guilty, we will direct and supervise the enforcement agency to ensure that trials such as imprisonment and fines are properly executed.\nInvestigative documents and courts are processed by the Office work stipulated by law.', 'Investigation, investigation\nProsecution\nStatements, cross-examinations, witness summons\nLaw application, punishment\nExecution management of fixed sentences', 'Law\nCase law', 'Prosecutor\'s Office\nCourt\nMinistry of Justice', 'Investigation\nGathering evidence\nProsecution decision\nProsecution\nTrial\nOpening statement\nEvidence submission\nWitness summons\nPenalty\nLaw enforcement supervision', 1, 1, 1, 1, '', '0.00', '0.00', '', 'None', '2,300 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 5, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:08:29', NULL),
(78, 'Judge', 7, 8, 22, 'Judges belong to the three legal profession (judges, prosecutors, lawyers), and are independent of power and have a neutral position.\n\nJudges are broadly divided into civil trials and criminal trials, and judges read the materials submitted in advance before proceeding to the trial.\nIn the trial, he listens to the parties, lawyers, prosecutors, witnesses, etc. and gives the judgment.\nIt is also the judge\'s role to issue arrest warrants and search and seizure warrants.\n\nJudges\' decisions are life-threatening and, as a case law, affect later trials, so they carry great responsibility.', 'The trials are roughly divided into civil trials and criminal trials. Through the trials, we listen to the parties, lawyers, prosecutors, witnesses, etc., check whether the evidence is valid, and make a judgment in the light of the law. I will give you.\nIn addition to making judgments, in civil cases we will adjust the interests of the parties and bring them to a settlement, and in domestic cases we will provide opportunities for related parties to discuss.\nIn criminal cases, not only the feelings of the victim, but also the role of guardian, such as quantifying the sentence in consideration of the accused\'s remorse and the possibility of rehabilitation.\nThe judge will read the indictment, record, evidence, etc. submitted in advance before proceeding to the trial.\nIt is also the judge\'s role to issue arrest warrants and search and seizure warrants.', 'Proceeding and management of trials\nObjective and impartial judgment\nApplication of literature, case law, and law\nPreparation of judgment', 'Constitution\nAdministrative law\nCivil Code\nCommercial Code\nCode of Civil Procedure\nPenal Code\nCode of Criminal Procedure', 'District court\nHigh Court\nsupreme court\nFamily court\nSummary court', 'Oral argument\nExamining evidence\nOral preparatory procedure\nFact-finding\nTrial\nDraft judgment\nJudgment\nHanding down', 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Lawyer (male)', '0