(79, 'Administrative scrivener', 7, 8, 22, 'As an administrative scrivener, as a document preparation professional, it is a job to consult, prepare, and apply for various documents at the request of individuals and corporations.\n\nIt is said that there are more than 10,000 types of documents to be consulted, prepared, and applied for, such as documents to be submitted to public offices, documents related to rights and obligations, and documents related to fact proof, and this is a job that requires specialized knowledge and experience.\nWhen preparing documents, we will meet with customers and grasp their requests, but if necessary, we will confirm with related parties and conduct on-site investigations, and prepare and apply for documents based on facts.\n\nThe image of an administrative scrivener is that he only prepares and applies for documents, but in reality, anyone under the control of an administrative scrivener can create documents, so the administrative scrivener himself has a lot of consulting work.', 'We will prepare documents to be submitted to public offices (each ministry, prefectural office, city / ward office, town / village office, police station, etc.) such as construction permit and restaurant permit.\nWe will create contract documents such as lease contracts and contract contracts, as well as documents related to rights and obligations such as heritage division agreements, content certification, and petition.\nWe will create documents related to fact proof, such as creating fact-based drawings and fact-based board meeting minutes.\nWhen preparing documents, we will meet with customers and grasp their requests, but if necessary, we will confirm with related parties and conduct on-site investigations, and prepare and apply for documents based on facts.\nWe provide consulting for documents that require specialized knowledge and experience.\nIf you are appointed as an adult guardian, we will protect you by concluding necessary contracts and managin