(81, 'Nursing care', 8, 2, 41, 'Long-term care office work is a job that performs all the office work necessary for facility management and long-term care services at insurance-covered facilities.\n\nOur main duties include long-term care fee billing, helper and equipment management, coordination with the national and local governments, and reception of family members and users. In particular, the long-term care invoice business is related to facility operation and income, and is a business that requires accuracy.\n\nDue to the increase in long-term care facilities accompanying the aging society, demand is increasing and many human resources are required.', 'I mainly work in insurance-covered facilities such as the Long-Term Care Health Facility, the Long-Term Care Health Facility, group homes, and day service centers, and work related to Office work.\nAs a long-term care fee claim business, we calculate the points of insurance coverage items according to the long-term care insurance system, create a long-term care fee invoice to the national and local governments, and calculate the burden on the user.\nAs management work, ordering work and management of nursing care supplies and equipment. It manages attendance, shifts, and payroll for employees and helpers.\nAs a coordination work, we will coordinate with related organizations such as the national government, local governments and medical institutions, and summarize each document. We may also support the work of the care manager, such as creating a care plan for the user.\nAs reception work, we perform reception work and telephone response for new users, explanation of facilities and usage procedures, receipt of service usage fees, and accounting work.', 'Document editing (MS, Google, etc.)\nOperation of long-term care software\nCalculation of the number of long-term care benefit units\nCreating a nursing care fee statement\nReceipt creation', 'Long-term care insurance system\nClaiming nursing care fees\nKnowledge