(87, 'Physician', 8, 2, 37, 'A physician is a specialist in clinical science centered on internal organs, and is responsible for improving and treating diseases from the inside of the body such as medicine and nutrition.\n\nIn order to find out the cause of the disorder, we will ask the patient for symptoms and perform an examination. Once the name of the disease has been identified, we will consider treatment and prepare injections, infusions, and drug prescriptions necessary for the treatment of injuries and illnesses.\n\nWhen a detailed examination or surgery is required, a small clinic often cannot handle it, so we may write a letter of introduction to a well-equipped hospital such as a university hospital.', 'In order to find out the cause of the disorder, we listen to the symptoms from the patient, listen to the heartbeat, measure the body temperature, and instruct the nurse or a specialized laboratory technician to collect blood or perform a detailed examination as needed.\nOnce the name of the disease has been identified, the treatment method will be examined according to the symptoms, and the nurse will be instructed to administer the drug, such as injections and infusions.\nWe will prepare a prescription that describes the type and amount of medicines necessary for the treatment of injuries and illnesses, and how to take them, and provide exercise and nutritional guidance.\nIf you need a detailed examination or major surgery, write a letter of introduction to a university hospital.\nIn large facilities such as university hospitals, the fields of specialization are subdivided. For example, if you are a gastroenterologist, you can analyze and diagnose symptoms and tests, as well as the necessary endoscopy and echography. We will perform the treatment that can be done under an endoscope.\nThe physician may also perform catheterization and some surgical procedures on his own.', 'Interviews, medical examinations, tests\ndiagnose\nTreatment\nOperation of medical record creation software\nCounseling\nTeam Management', 'Medical Practitioners Act\nBasic medicine\nClinical medicine\nSocial medicine\nInternal medical expertise', 'Hospital\nUniversity hospital\nClinic\nResearch Institute\nCorporate', 'Interview\nConsultation\nIdentification\nInformed consent\nTreatment, treatment\nprescription\nCreating a medical record\nPrognosis observation', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Doctor (male)', '36.40', '967.20', 'Starting salary: 364,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 806,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'Graduated from the 6 -year dentistry or dental university and take clinical training for more than one year after passing the national exam.', '77,880 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:09:33', NULL),
(88, 'Nurse', 8, 2, 39, 'A nurse is a job that resides in hospitals, clinics, long-term care facilities, etc., and assists in the examination and treatment of patients as a member of the medical team.\n\nWe measure the patient\'s physical condition, collect blood, perform necessary care for the patient such as injections and infusions, and record the contents in the medical record.\nFor inpatients, we also provide bathing assistance and meal assistance. In the case of hospitals, there are day shifts and night shifts.\n\nIn recent years, medical specialization has progressed, and team medical care, in which nurses also form a team with doctors, pharmacists, nutritionists, etc., is also advancing, and nurses are important as being closest to patients. Take a role.\nUntil a long time ago, it was called Angel in a white coat and was a profession centered on women, but in recent years the number of men has increased dramatically because it is a job that requires physical strength.', 'Vital sign measurements and tests such as blood pressure, body temperature, pulse measurement and blood sampling are performed and recorded in the medical record for the purpose of grasping the patient\'s physical condition and follow-up.\nWe will provide the necessary assistance to the patient, such as injections and infusions necessary for treatment, and record the treatment details in the medical record.\nWe perform preparations and records necessary for surgery and treatment, and accept new patients.\nWe provide medicine distribution and bathing assistance for inpatients, meal preparation, meal assistance, and reception of visitors.\nThere are day shifts and night shifts, and when changing, nurses gather to share patient information and take over.', 'Dietary assistance\nExcretion assistance\nActivity / rest support\nCleanliness and clothing life support\nAdjust breathing and circulation\nWound management\nDrug administration\nLifesaving first aid\nSymptom / biological function management