(89, 'Pharmacist', 8, 2, 38, 'A pharmacist is a job that dispenses and provides necessary medicines to patients, mainly at dispensing pharmacies and drug stores, according to the doctor\'s prescription.\n\nWe will dispense the medicine according to the prescription given by the doctor and give guidance such as advice on how to take it. We manage the patient\'s medication history in the medication notebook and database, and pay close attention to swallowing and allergies. Some pharmacists work for medical institutions, and sometimes work as Self-Defense Force pharmacists or drug control officers at health centers and laboratories.\n\nAt pharmaceutical companies, there are also people who are active as researchers who research and develop drugs and new drugs, and MRs who explain drugs at medical institutions.', 'At dispensing pharmacies and drug stores, medicines are dispensed according to the prescription issued by the doctor, and the patient is instructed to take the medicine, such as advice on how to take it.\nEach patient\'s medication history is managed in a database, and the medication is dispensed after checking the medication notebook and paying close attention to swallowing and allergies.\nA pharmacist who works for a drug-related company also conducts research and development of drugs, work related to clinical trials that are clinical trials of new drugs, and MRs that explain drugs to medical institutions.\nAt school, I belong to Hygiene management such as pools and cafeterias, sports teams, etc., and sometimes provide doping support and supplement guidance.', 'Dispensing\nMedication guidance and consultation\nOperation of drug history management software\nCounseling', 'Physics\nChemistry (organic, biological)\nOrganism\nHygiene\nEpidemiology\nPharmacology\nDrug\nRegulations / systems / ethics\nDispensing', 'Dispensing pharmacy\nHospital\nPharmaceutical company\nDrug store\nCosmetic company\nBio-related company\nResearch Institute\nGovernment office', 'Recei