(90, 'Childminder', 8, 2, 36, 'A nursery teacher is a childcare center or child welfare facility that mainly takes care of children aged 0 to 6 years old.\n\nFrom preparations for opening to the closing of the park, where parents are picked up, we will protect children\'s safety, support healthy growth, and carry out curriculum such as exercise and learning.\nWe carry out a wide range of tasks such as planning and preparing frequent recreational activities such as festivals, athletic meet, and recitals, and managing the day.\n\nIt is important for nursery teachers not only to protect children both physically and mentally, but also to think and practice play that attracts children\'s interests and to develop their thinking ability and sensibility.', 'Childcare centers and child welfare facilities mainly care for children aged 0 to 6 years.\nIn preparation for the opening of the park, we will welcome the children by cleaning the room, ventilating, checking the schedule, morning assembly of the staff, etc. before the children go to the park in the morning.\nIn the morning, we will give morning greetings, confirm attendance, and do gymnastics. Activities such as free play and walks are carried out according to the program of the day.\nAt noon, we encourage children to wash their hands and gargle before lunch, prepare together, and eat together while watching the children. After lunch, we will clean up with the children and support them in brushing their teeth and toilets.\nFrom the afternoon to the evening, practice recreation and events such as naps, athletic meet, presentations, festivals, etc. By the time parents are picked up, observe each person\'s behavior and emotional movements and fill out a contact book. I will tell the parents about the situation of the day and the matters to be contacted.\nIn preparation for closing the park, after seeing off the children, we will clean and tidy up the park and close the doors.\nFrom the situation of children\'s injuries and