(91, 'Elementary school teacher', 8, 2, 42, 'Elementary school teachers make lesson plans in accordance with the standards of the Course of Study established by the Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology, and provide guidance on subjects.\n\nBasically, all subjects are taught by one person, but some schools have teachers specializing in music and physical education.\nWe will prepare for the lesson before the students go to school and respond to attendance. After commuting to school, classes will be held in the morning and afternoon, and after leaving the school, the students will be graded for the test and prepared for the next day\'s class.\nIn addition, we prepare and carry out school events such as athletic meet and music concert, and carry out PTA activities.\n\nIn the past, most of the classes were taught by one teacher as a teacher, but in recent years, an initiative called Teaching, a team that teaches one class with two teachers, is also progressing.', 'We will formulate a lesson plan and provide guidance on subjects in accordance with the standards of the Course of Study established by the Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology so that all children can receive a certain level of education.\nSome elementary school teachers have teachers who specialize in music and physical education, but basically they teach all subjects such as Japanese language, math, science, and society by themselves, and have lunch in the morning, afternoon, and lunch. Classes from the 4th to the 6th period will be held.\nAfter going to work in the morning, we will prepare for classes, score tests, and respond to attendance notifications from parents.\nI always communicate with my students and consult with them if they have any problems not only in the school but also in their homes and relationships.\nAfter the afternoon lessons and cleaning, we will have a return party to send the children out of school, and then we will score the test and prepare for the next day\'s lessons.\nWe hold regular interviews with parents every semester to understand what the students are doing at home and to communicate with them about the students in the class.\nIf you become an advisor for club activities, we will prepare, guide and carry out activities.\nWe prepare and carry out various school events such as school excursions, excursions, extracurricular lessons, athletic meet, and music concerts, as well as PTA activities.', 'Text and test creation\nTeaching\nCoaching\nCounseling\nClassroom management\nCommunication\nSubject guidance', 'Education\nEducational psychology\nNational language\nArithmetic\nScience\nSociety\nPhysical education\nMusic\nHome\nDrawing\nLife\nEnglish', 'National elementary school\nPublic elementary school\nPrivate elementary school', 'Subject guidance\nLife and moral guidance\nTest creation and scoring\nPlanning and management of events and events\nGrade, class management\nPTA activity\nClub activity guidance\nEducation meeting', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'High school teacher (male)', '26.30', '619.20', 'Starting salary: 263,000 yen (company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 516,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', 'Completing a teaching course at a school with a teaching professional course', '410,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:09:58', NULL),
(92, 'Private / public high school teacher', 8, 2, 43, 'High school teachers work in public and private high schools, take charge of classes, and provide education and guidance on the subjects they specialize in.\n\nUnlike elementary and junior high schools, high school teachers are in charge of specialized subjects and teach across classes.\nIn my class, I set up an annual lesson schedule, get career counseling, always communicate with students, and get counseling if I have any problems.\nIn addition, if you become an advisor for club activities, we will prepare, instruct, and carry out activities, and support the students who will be the main players at sports festivals and school festivals.\n\nThere are no classes during long vacations, but there are supplementary lessons and classes for second and third graders, so I take about two lessons a day. In addition, we will prepare for an open campus for junior high school students and a school festival together with the students. Of course, if you are an advisor for club activities, we will also provide club activity guidance.', 'Unlike elementary and junior high schools, high school teachers are in charge of specialized subjects and are conducted across classes.\nBefore the start of the new semester, we will formulate an annual lesson schedule such as quizzes, mid-term exams, and final exams in your class.\nStudents in their homeroom class will be investigated on their career paths, and will be given guidance and consultation on study methods and electives that suit their wishes.\nWe hold regular interviews with parents every semester to understand what the students are doing at home and to communicate with them about the students in the class.\nI always communicate with my students, and if I have any concerns about not only classes but also relationships and her family life, I will consult with them.\nIf you become an advisor for club activities, we will prepare, guide and carry out activities.\nSports festivals and