(93, 'Truck driver', 8, 2, 7, 'A truck driver is the job of driving a truck to reliably deliver luggage requested by individuals or corporations from the unloading location to the unloading location.\n\nThere are various types such as parcels such as Takkyubin, large structures used for construction from moving luggage, gasoline and high pressure gas designated as dangerous goods, and small, medium, large, long distance, home delivery, refrigerated trucks according to it. The type and required license will vary depending on the truck used, load capacity, distance, etc., such as tank trucks and tank trucks.\n\nThe harsh working environment of truck drivers has been a problem for some time, but recently, the environment has gradually become easier to work, such as shortening working hours and taking paid leave.', 'There are various types of truck drivers, such as small and medium-sized trucks and heavy-duty trucks, long-distance trucks, home delivery, refrigerated trucks, tank trucks, etc., depending on the truck used, load capacity, distance, etc.\nLuggage to be carried varies from parcels such as Takkyubin to large structures used for construction, gasoline and high-pressure gas designated as dangerous goods at the request of individuals and corporations.\nNot only transportation, but also unloading and unloading, loading the luggage on the truck at the unloading place, unloading the carried luggage when it arrives, and carrying out the delivery procedure.\nSince a license is the lifeline of work, it is even more necessary to be safe and comply with the rules so that it will not be suspended or revoked. As for a driver\'s license, a normal license is required for light trucks up to 2 tons, a medium-sized vehicle license is required for vehicles of 5 tons or more and less than 11 tons, and a large vehicle license is required for 11 tons or more. Obtaining or renewing a license is also an important task.', 'Safe drive\nLoading (unloading)', 'Vehicle features\nHow to m