(94, 'Aircraft pilot (captain / co -pilot)', 8, 2, 7, 'Aircraft pilots are the job of maneuvering passenger and freighters to safely transport people and cargo to their destinations.\n\nBefore departure, we will grasp the weather data, the condition of the airport, the maintenance status of the aircraft, etc., and prepare for takeoff by sharing the work between the captain and the co-pilot.\nWhen the room is ready and you are instructed to take off, take off. During the flight, based on the flight plan, we will contact the air traffic controller to confirm safe navigation. After landing, we will inform the maintenance staff of the condition of the aircraft in flight, look back on the flight, and write a flight diary.\n\nRecently, with the development of autonomous driving systems, driving has become relatively easy and the burden on pilots has been reduced, while the development of cheaper private jets and the like has progressed, and the demand for aircraft pilots is expected to further increase. I will.', 'Before boarding the aircraft to be operated, we will meet with the operation manager, co-pilot, and cabin attendant to check weather data, airport conditions, aircraft maintenance status, flight altitude, fuel, and so on.\nIn the cockpit after boarding, the captain and the co-pilot will share the tasks such as inputting flight data to the equipment, checking fuel and instruments, and preparing for engine start.\nWhen the room is ready, we will wirelessly communicate with the air traffic controller and take off when instructed to take off.\nWhile flying based on the flight plan, we will keep in touch with the air traffic controller to ensure safety by changing the course if there is a risk of large airflow turbulence or lightning strikes.\nDuring the flight, we will continue to check the instruments and radar for engine and equipment troubles and fuel shortages.\nAfter landing, we will inform the maintenance staff of the condition of the aircraft, look back on the flight, and write a flight diary.', 'Maneuvering skills\nWeather map reading comprehension\nRadio operation\nForeign language conversation\nTeam Management', 'Language\nAerodynamics\nAviation engineering\nAviation regulations\nAeronautical meteorology\nAviation physiology\nRadio engineering', 'Airlines\nGovernment office\nShipping company\nSurveying company\nMedia', 'Briefing\nPreparing for takeoff\nManeuver\nDebriefing', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Aircraft pilot (male)', '23.30', '964.80', 'Starting salary: 233,000 yen (Company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 804,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age meter)', '・ Physical conditions\n・ Enroll in a pilot training school operated by the airline as a trainee or Graduate from Aerospella\n\nDepending on the job content, one of the following is required\n・ Regular transportation pilot\n・ Associate operational pilot\n・ Business pilot\n・ Private pilot', '5,930 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 8, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:10:18', NULL),
(95, 'Cabin attendant', 11, 9, 31, 'A cabin attendant (flight attendant) is the job of boarding a passenger plane, providing services so that passengers can spend their time comfortably, and managing security.\n\nBefore boarding a passenger plane, meet with flight managers and pilots to check weather data and flight plans. After boarding, we will prepare your room and welcome passengers.\nFrom boarding to disembarking, we will explain the in-flight equipment and equipment, announce the operation status, eat and drink, and provide newspapers and magazines so that passengers can spend their time safely and comfortably.\nProtecting the safety of passengers is also one of the important tasks, and in cooperation with the pilot, we will provide in-flight precautions, explanations of emergencies, first aid for sudden illnesses, and guidance in emergencies.\n\nThe image of a female cabin attendant is strong, but in recent years there has been an increasing need for a male cabin attendant who can respond more effectively in the event of an emergency such as hijacking.', 'Before boarding a passenger aircraft, we will meet with operation managers and pilots to check weather data, airport conditions, aircraft maintenance status and flight plans.\nBefore passengers board, we will check seats, equipment, cleaning conditions, etc. and prepare the cabin.\nWe provide seat guidance when passengers board a passenger plane, and check for lost items and see-off when getting off.\nWe will always pay attention to the explanation of the in-flight equipment and the equipment around the seats, the announcement of the operation status, the food and drink, and the provision of newspapers and magazines so that we can spend our time safely and comfortably on the plane.\nIn order to protect the safety of passengers, we will carry out security management such as in-flight precautions, explanations in emergencies, first aid for suddenly ill people, and guidance in emergencies.\nWe will collect garbage from the flight and clean the seats and washrooms.\nIn cooperation with pilots, we will broadcast in-flight broadcasts such as weather and operating conditions, and guide passengers to wear seat belts when sudden shaking such as changes in airflow is expected.', 'Customer service\nMakeup and grooming\nsign language\nIn-flight broadcast\nSafety management\nHygiene management\ncleaning', 'Language\nSecurity knowledge\nCustoms of various countries\nAircraft model and features\nFlight theory', 'Airlines', 'Briefing\nBoarding preparation\nBoarding information\nIn-flight customer service\nOffering food and drink\nSee off\nCleaning. Lost and Found Confirmation\nDebriefing', 0, 0, 0, 1, 'Aircraft flight attendant (female)', '29.00', '496.80', 'Starting salary: 290,000 yen (company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 414,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age total) ', '・ Age conditions\n・ Physical conditions\n・ Residential conditions\n・ TOEIC score', '16,000 people', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 7, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:10:25', NULL),
(96, 'Art dealer', 11, 9, 30, 'Called an art dealer or art dealer, it is the job of purchasing art and selling it to customers at exhibitions, department store galleries, and art galleries.\n\nWe go to auctions, visit peers, collectors, and artists to determine if a work of art is valuable and sell, buy it, and sell it to our customer\'s collectors.\nIn addition, art dealers with exhibition spaces and art dealers working in the art department of department stores sell their works, plan and hold exhibitions of new works, and play a role in nurturing artists as a place to disseminate new works of art. increase.\n\nIn the past, there were many purchase requests from individuals, but recently, inquiries from antique dealers such as precious metal purchase shops are increasing.', 'We go to auctions, visit peers, collectors, and artists to determine if an art piece is valuable and sellable, and then buy it.\nThe purchased works of art are sold to customer collectors at exhibitions, department store galleries, and art galleries.\nAn art dealer who has an exhibition space and an art dealer who works in the art department of a department store sells works and also plans and holds exhibitions of new works, and also plays a role of nurturing artists as a place to disseminate new works of art.\nWe will constantly collect information on our specialty and deepen our knowledge and experience.\nIn order to judge the value of works of art and appraisal of antique works of art, we will learn the knowledge of various works and learn how to distinguish the values.', 'Appraisal\nBusiness building\nPresentation\nCommunication\nNegotiation', 'Wide knowledge of art in general\nKnowledge of a specific field\nArt history\nMarketing', 'Department store\nTrading company\nGallery\nCharacter\nMuseum\nAntique dealer', '≪Auction≫\nInformation gathering and examination\nSuccessful bid, purchase\n≪Individual purchase≫\nChecking goods and condition\nMarket research\nEvaluation\nNegotiation\nPurchase\