(99, 'Hairdresser', 8, 2, 34, 'A hairdresser, also known as a hair stylist, is the job of arranging hair beautifully according to the needs of customers at a beauty salon.\n\nWe will confirm the customer\'s request and discuss and decide the styling such as hairstyle and color in advance.\nCut while looking at the overall balance, and when all the treatments are finished, set it neatly.\n\nIn addition, we will introduce and sell nail care products that suit our customers, and will also inform you about campaigns and events other than when you come to the store.\n\nRecently, the number of beauty salons that carry out total beauty and perform treatments related to parts other than hair, such as makeup and nails, is increasing.', 'We will confirm the customer\'s request for what hairstyle and color they want, and discuss and decide on the styling. Once you have decided on the desired styling, cut while looking at the overall balance, and finally set.\nIn addition to shampoos and treatments, we also apply color and change hair color or perm according to customer\'s request.\nWe prepare linen and equipment to be used in the treatment before opening, confirm and accept reservations, manage product inventory, and clean and clean up after closing.\nWe will propose and sell hair care products that suit the customer who also used it for styling.\nIn addition to when you come to the store, we will guide you through product and service campaigns and events, and follow up with you through the smartphone app.\nWe will practice using cut models and mannequins to improve styling skills and acquire the latest styles.', 'Shampoo\nHaircut\nColouring\nPerm\nHair set\nCommunication\nCounseling\nCustomer service', 'Cosmetology-related regulations\nHygiene management\nCosmetology health\nPhysics, chemistry\nCosmetology theory', 'Beauty salon\nHotel\nBridal salon', 'Counseling\nShampoo blow\nCut\nColouring\nPerm\nSet', 0, 0, 0, 0, '① Barber / Hairdresser (female), ② Barber / Hairdresser (f