(100, 'Interpreter', 11, 9, 31, 'Interpreting is the job of translating languages by using the languages of two or more countries and intervening between people who do not understand each other.\n\nSimultaneous interpretation, which interprets at almost the same pace as the speaker\'s speech, and sequential interpretation, in which words are separated for interpretation, are performed by the speaker.\nIn addition, simultaneous interpretation will be provided by a whispering interpreter who stands next to the listener and translates by ear, and an accompanying interpreter who accompanies sightseeing and shopping. If you want to provide an accompanying interpreter for a fee, you need to be qualified as an interpreter guide.\n\nRecently, portable devices and smartphone apps dedicated to interpreting that are compatible with several countries have appeared, and their accuracy is improving day by day. It is required to convey the intention and background of the smartphone.', 'In sequential interpretation, the speaker speaks by separating words for each sentence, and the interpreter interprets the contents of that part.\nSimultaneous interpretation involves listening to the speaker\'s words and at the same time translating into another language.\nEven with simultaneous interpretation, whispering interpretation will be performed by standing next to the listener and translating at a volume that is whispering at the ear.\nWe will provide an accompanying interpreter who will accompany you for sightseeing and shopping while interpreting with your guide. If you want to provide an accompanying interpreter for a fee, you need to be qualified as an interpreter guide.\nIn order to understand the speaker\'s habits and accents in advance, check the place of origin and profile, and prepare in advance so that the speaker\'s words can be conveyed accurately.\nIn order to convey not only the superficial words but also the intentions and purposes behind the words, we will acquire various knowledge such as the history, culture, customs and proverbs unique to the country.', 'Listening\nForeign language conversation\nNative language conversation\nCommunication', 'Language\nUnderstanding different cultures\nKnowledge of the scene of interpreting', 'Interpreter agent\nInternational Conference Hall\nBroadcaster', 'Prior research\nListening\nInterpretation', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Reporter (male)', '32.50', '750.00', 'Starting salary: 325,000 yen (company size total, 20-24 years old)\nAverage: 625,000 yen (1,000 people or more, age total)', 'Business interpreter test', 'Not clear', '', '', '', '', 1, 1, 9, 0, NOW(), '2019-03-05 16:11:01', NULL),
